578 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_oldLeEnabled __attribute__((section(".retention")));
579 FTDF_Time FTDF_rzTime __attribute__((section(".retention")));
580 FTDF_ShortAddress FTDF_sendFramePending __attribute__((section(".retention")));
581 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
582 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
583 uint32_t FTDF_curTime[ 2 ] __attribute__((section(".retention")));
584 FTDF_LmacCounters FTDF_lmacCounters __attribute__((section(".retention")));
585 FTDF_FrameHeader FTDF_fh;
586 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
587 FTDF_SecurityHeader FTDF_sh;
588 FTDF_AssocAdmin FTDF_aa;
589 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
590 
591 #if FTDF_USE_PTI
592 /* Packet traffic information used when FTDF is in RX enable. */
593 static FTDF_PTI FTDF_RxPti __attribute__((section(".retention")));
594 #endif
595 static void sendConfirm(FTDF_Status status,
596  FTDF_MsgId msgId);
597 
598 void FTDF_reset(int setDefaultPIB)
599 {
600  if (setDefaultPIB)
601  {
602  // Reset PIB values to their default values
603  memset(&FTDF_pib, 0, sizeof(FTDF_pib));
604 
605  FTDF_pib.extAddress = FTDF_GET_EXT_ADDRESS();
606  FTDF_pib.ackWaitDuration = 0x36;
607 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
608  FTDF_pib.autoRequest = FTDF_TRUE;
609  FTDF_pib.beaconOrder = 15;
610  FTDF_pib.DSN = FTDF_pib.extAddress & 0xff;
611  FTDF_pib.BSN = FTDF_pib.extAddress & 0xff;
612  FTDF_pib.EBSN = FTDF_pib.extAddress & 0xff;
613  FTDF_pib.coordShortAddress = 0xffff;
614 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
615  FTDF_pib.maxBE = 5;
616  FTDF_pib.maxCSMABackoffs = 4;
617  FTDF_pib.maxFrameTotalWaitTime = 1026; // see asic_vol v40.100.2.30 PR2540
618  FTDF_pib.maxFrameRetries = 3;
619  FTDF_pib.minBE = 3;
620 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
621  FTDF_pib.LIFSPeriod = 40;
622  FTDF_pib.SIFSPeriod = 12;
623 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
624  FTDF_pib.PANId = 0xffff;
625 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
626  FTDF_pib.responseWaitTime = 32;
627 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
628  FTDF_pib.shortAddress = 0xffff;
629 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
630  FTDF_pib.superframeOrder = 15;
631  FTDF_pib.timestampSupported = FTDF_TRUE;
632  FTDF_pib.transactionPersistenceTime = 0x1f4;
633  FTDF_pib.enhAckWaitDuration = 0x360;
634  FTDF_pib.EBAutoSA = FTDF_AUTO_FULL;
635 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
636  FTDF_pib.currentChannel = 11;
637  FTDF_pib.CCAMode = FTDF_CCA_MODE_1;
638 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
639  FTDF_pib.maxFrameDuration = FTDF_TBD;
640  FTDF_pib.SHRDuration = FTDF_TBD;
641  FTDF_pib.frameCounterMode = 4;
642 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
643  FTDF_pib.metricsCapable = FTDF_TRUE;
644 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
645  FTDF_pib.beaconAutoRespond = FTDF_TRUE;
646 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
647  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.counterOctets = 4; // 32 bit counters
648 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
649  FTDF_pib.joinPriority = 1;
650  FTDF_pib.slotframeTable.slotframeEntries = FTDF_slotframeTable;
651  FTDF_pib.linkTable.linkEntries = FTDF_linkTable;
652  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsCCAOffset = 1800;
653  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsCCA = 128;
654  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsTxOffset = 2120;
655  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsRxOffset = 1020;
656  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsRxAckDelay = 800;
657  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsTxAckDelay = 1000;
658  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsRxWait = 2200;
659  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsAckWait = 400;
660  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsRxTx = 192;
661  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsMaxAck = 2400;
662  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsMaxTs = 4256;
663  FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsTimeslotLength = 10000;
664  FTDF_pib.tsSyncCorrectThreshold = 220;
665  FTDF_pib.hoppingSequenceLength = 16;
666 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
667  int i;
668 
669  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_PTIS; i++)
670  {
671  FTDF_pib.ptiConfig.ptis[i] = 0;
672  }
673 
674 #endif
675 #ifdef FTDF_NO_CSL
676  FTDF_pib.LECapable = FTDF_FALSE;
677 #else
678  FTDF_pib.LECapable = FTDF_TRUE;
679 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
680 #ifdef FTDF_NO_TSCH
681  FTDF_pib.tschCapable = FTDF_FALSE;
682 #else
683  FTDF_pib.tschCapable = FTDF_TRUE;
684 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
685 
686  int n;
687 
688  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_MAX_HOPPING_SEQUENCE_LENGTH; n++)
689  {
690  FTDF_pib.hoppingSequenceList[ n ] = n + 11;
691  }
692 
693 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
694 
695  FTDF_transparentMode = FTDF_FALSE;
696 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
697  FTDF_isPANCoordinator = FTDF_FALSE;
698 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
699  FTDF_lmacCounters.fcsErrorCnt = 0;
700  FTDF_lmacCounters.txStdAckCnt = 0;
701  FTDF_lmacCounters.rxStdAckCnt = 0;
702 
703 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
704  memset(FTDF_pib.defaultKeySource, 0xff, 8);
705 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
706 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
707  FTDF_pib.boIrqThreshold = FTDF_BO_IRQ_THRESHOLD;
708 #endif /* #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A */
709  }
710 
711  FTDF_initQueues();
712 
713  volatile uint32_t *lmacReset = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMACRESET);
714  *lmacReset = MSK_R_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMACRESET;
715 
716  volatile uint32_t *controlStatus = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMAC_CONTROL_STATUS);
717  uint32_t wait = 0;
718 
719  while ((*controlStatus & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMACREADY4SLEEP) == 0)
720  {
721  wait++;
722  }
723 
724  volatile uint32_t *wakeupTimerEnableStatus = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLESTATUS);
725 
726 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV == BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
727  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ALWAYS_ON_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLE, 0);
728 
729 #else
730  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLE_CLEAR, 1);
731 #endif
732 
733  while (*wakeupTimerEnableStatus & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLESTATUS)
734  { }
735 
736 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV == BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
737  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ALWAYS_ON_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLE, 1);
738 
739 #else
740  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLE_SET, 1);
741 #endif
742 
743  while ((*wakeupTimerEnableStatus & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_WAKEUPTIMERENABLESTATUS) == 0)
744  { }
745 
746 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
747  int n;
748 
749 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
750 
751  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS; n++)
752  {
753  FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].addr = 0xffff;
754  }
755 
756  FTDF_oldLeEnabled = FTDF_FALSE;
757  FTDF_wakeUpEnableLe = FTDF_FALSE;
758  FTDF_sendFramePending = 0xfffe;
759 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
760 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
761  FTDF_txInProgress = FTDF_FALSE;
762 
763  FTDF_initCurTime64();
764 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
765  FTDF_initTschRetries();
766  FTDF_initBackoff();
767 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
768 
769 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
770 
771  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_RX_ADDRS; n++)
772  {
773  FTDF_rxa[ n ].addrMode = FTDF_NO_ADDRESS;
774  FTDF_rxa[ n ].dsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
775  FTDF_rxa[ n ].bsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
776  FTDF_rxa[ n ].ebsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
777  }
778 
779 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
780 
781  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_NEIGHBORS; n++)
782  {
783  FTDF_neighborTable[ n ].dstAddr = 0xffff;
784  }
785 
786 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
787 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
788 #if FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF
789  FTDF_sdbFsmReset();
790 #endif /* FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF */
791  FTDF_initLmac();
792 
793 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
794  FTDF_rzTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
795 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
796 
797 #if dg_configUSE_FTDF_DDPHY == 1
798  FTDF_ddphySet(0);
799 #endif
800 }
801 
802 #ifndef FTDF_PHY_API
803 void FTDF_processResetRequest(FTDF_ResetRequest *resetRequest)
804 {
805 
806  FTDF_reset(resetRequest->setDefaultPIB);
807  FTDF_ResetConfirm *resetConfirm = (FTDF_ResetConfirm *) FTDF_GET_MSG_BUFFER(sizeof(FTDF_ResetConfirm));
808 
809  resetConfirm->msgId = FTDF_RESET_CONFIRM;
810  resetConfirm->status = FTDF_SUCCESS;
811 
812  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) resetRequest);
813 
814  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) resetConfirm);
815 }
816 #endif /* FTDF_PHY_API */
817 
818 void FTDF_initLmac(void)
819 {
820  FTDF_PIBAttribute PIBAttribute;
821 
822  for (PIBAttribute = 1; PIBAttribute <= FTDF_NR_OF_PIB_ATTRIBUTES; PIBAttribute++)
823  {
824  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].setFunc != NULL)
825  {
826  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].setFunc();
827  }
828  }
829 
830  if (FTDF_transparentMode == FTDF_TRUE)
831  {
832  FTDF_enableTransparentMode(FTDF_TRUE, FTDF_transparentModeOptions);
833  }
834 
835 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
836 
837  if (FTDF_isPANCoordinator)
838  {
839  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_ISPANCOORDINATOR, 1);
840  }
841 
842 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
843  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CCAIDLEWAIT, 192);
844 
845  volatile uint32_t *txFlagClear = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_CLEAR);
846  *txFlagClear = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_CLEAR;
847 
848  volatile uint32_t *phyParams = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHY_PARAMETERS_2);
849  *phyParams = (FTDF_PHYTXSTARTUP << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYTXSTARTUP) |
850  (FTDF_PHYTXLATENCY << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYTXLATENCY) |
851  (FTDF_PHYTXFINISH << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYTXFINISH) |
852  (FTDF_PHYTRXWAIT << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYTRXWAIT);
853 
854  phyParams = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHY_PARAMETERS_3);
855  *phyParams = (FTDF_PHYRXSTARTUP << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYRXSTARTUP) |
856  (FTDF_PHYRXLATENCY << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYRXLATENCY) |
857  (FTDF_PHYENABLE << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYENABLE);
858 
859  volatile uint32_t *ftdfCm = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_FTDF_CM);
860  *ftdfCm = FTDF_MSK_TX_CE | FTDF_MSK_RX_CE | FTDF_MSK_SYMBOL_TMR_CE;
861 
862  volatile uint32_t *rxMask = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_MASK);
863  *rxMask = MSK_R_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_MASK;
864 
865  volatile uint32_t *lmacMask = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMAC_MASK);
866  *lmacMask = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXTIMEREXPIRED_M;
867 
868  volatile uint32_t *lmacCtrlMask = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMAC_CONTROL_MASK);
869  *lmacCtrlMask = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR_M |
870  MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIME2THR_M |
871  MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYNCTIMESTAMP_M;
872 
873  volatile uint32_t *txFlagClearM;
874  txFlagClearM = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_CLEAR_M, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
875  *txFlagClearM |= MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_CLEAR_M;
876  txFlagClearM = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_CLEAR_M, FTDF_TX_WAKEUP_BUFFER);
877  *txFlagClearM |= MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_CLEAR_M;
878 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
879 #if FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO
880  FTDF_fpprReset();
881  FTDF_fpprSetMode(FTDF_TRUE, FTDF_FALSE, FTDF_FALSE);
882 #else
883  FTDF_fpprSetMode(FTDF_FALSE, FTDF_TRUE, FTDF_TRUE);
884 #endif /* #if FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO */
885 #if FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF
886  /* Unmask long BO interrupt. */
887  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_THR_M, 1);
888 #else /* FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF */
889  /* Set BO threshold. */
890  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_THRESHOLD, FTDF_BO_IRQ_THRESHOLD);
891 
892  /* Mask long BO interrupt. */
893  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_THR_M, 0);
894 #endif /* FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF */
895 #if FTDF_USE_LPDP == 1
896  FTDF_lpdpEnable(FTDF_TRUE);
897 #endif /* #if FTDF_USE_LPDP == 1 */
898 #endif /* #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A */
899 }
900 
901 #ifdef FTDF_PHY_API
902 FTDF_PIBAttributeValue *FTDF_getValue(FTDF_PIBAttribute PIBAttribute)
903 {
904 
905  if (PIBAttribute <= FTDF_NR_OF_PIB_ATTRIBUTES &&
906  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr != NULL)
907  {
908  // Update PIB attribute with current LMAC status if a getFunc is defined
909  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].getFunc != NULL)
910  {
911  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].getFunc();
912  }
913 
914  return pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr;
915  }
916 
917  return NULL;
918 }
919 
920 FTDF_Status FTDF_setValue(FTDF_PIBAttribute PIBAttribute, const FTDF_PIBAttributeValue *PIBAttributeValue)
921 {
922  if (PIBAttribute <= FTDF_NR_OF_PIB_ATTRIBUTES &&
923  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr != NULL)
924  {
925  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].size != 0)
926  {
927  memcpy(pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr,
928  PIBAttributeValue,
929  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].size);
930 
931  // Update LMAC with new PIB attribute value if a setFunc is defined
932  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].setFunc != NULL)
933  {
934  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].setFunc();
935  }
936 
937  return FTDF_SUCCESS;
938 
939  }
940  else
941  {
942  return FTDF_READ_ONLY;
943  }
944  }
945 
946  return FTDF_UNSUPPORTED_ATTRIBUTE;
947 }
948 
949 #else /* FTDF_PHY_API */
950 void FTDF_processGetRequest(FTDF_GetRequest *getRequest)
951 {
952  FTDF_GetConfirm *getConfirm = (FTDF_GetConfirm *) FTDF_GET_MSG_BUFFER(sizeof(FTDF_GetConfirm));
953  FTDF_PIBAttribute PIBAttribute = getRequest->PIBAttribute;
954 
955  getConfirm->msgId = FTDF_GET_CONFIRM;
956  getConfirm->PIBAttribute = PIBAttribute;
957 
958  if (PIBAttribute <= FTDF_NR_OF_PIB_ATTRIBUTES &&
959  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr != NULL)
960  {
961  // Update PIB attribute with current LMAC status if a getFunc is defined
962  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].getFunc != NULL)
963  {
964  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].getFunc();
965  }
966 
967  getConfirm->status = FTDF_SUCCESS;
968  getConfirm->PIBAttributeValue = pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr;
969  }
970  else
971  {
972  getConfirm->status = FTDF_UNSUPPORTED_ATTRIBUTE;
973  }
974 
975  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) getRequest);
976 
977  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) getConfirm);
978 }
979 
980 void FTDF_processSetRequest(FTDF_SetRequest *setRequest)
981 {
982  FTDF_SetConfirm *setConfirm = (FTDF_SetConfirm *) FTDF_GET_MSG_BUFFER(sizeof(FTDF_SetConfirm));
983  FTDF_PIBAttribute PIBAttribute = setRequest->PIBAttribute;
984 
985  setConfirm->msgId = FTDF_SET_CONFIRM;
986  setConfirm->PIBAttribute = PIBAttribute;
987 
988  if (PIBAttribute <= FTDF_NR_OF_PIB_ATTRIBUTES &&
989  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr != NULL)
990  {
991  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].size != 0)
992  {
993  setConfirm->status = FTDF_SUCCESS;
994  memcpy(pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].addr,
995  setRequest->PIBAttributeValue,
996  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].size);
997 
998  // Update LMAC with new PIB attribute value if a setFunc is defined
999  if (pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].setFunc != NULL)
1000  {
1001  pibAttributeTable.attributeDefs[ PIBAttribute ].setFunc();
1002  }
1003  }
1004  else
1005  {
1006  setConfirm->status = FTDF_READ_ONLY;
1007  }
1008  }
1009  else
1010  {
1011  setConfirm->status = FTDF_UNSUPPORTED_ATTRIBUTE;
1012  }
1013 
1014  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) setRequest);
1015 
1016  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) setConfirm);
1017 }
1018 
1019 
1020 void FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(FTDF_MsgBuffer *request,
1021  FTDF_Status status,
1022  FTDF_PANId PANId,
1023  FTDF_AddressMode srcAddrMode,
1024  FTDF_Address srcAddr,
1025  FTDF_AddressMode dstAddrMode,
1026  FTDF_Address dstAddr,
1027  FTDF_SecurityLevel securityLevel,
1028  FTDF_KeyIdMode keyIdMode,
1029  FTDF_Octet *keySource,
1030  FTDF_KeyIndex keyIndex)
1031 {
1032  FTDF_CommStatusIndication *commStatus =
1033  (FTDF_CommStatusIndication *) FTDF_GET_MSG_BUFFER(sizeof(FTDF_CommStatusIndication));
1034 
1035  commStatus->msgId = FTDF_COMM_STATUS_INDICATION;
1036  commStatus->PANId = PANId;
1037  commStatus->srcAddrMode = srcAddrMode;
1038  commStatus->srcAddr = srcAddr;
1039  commStatus->dstAddrMode = dstAddrMode;
1040  commStatus->dstAddr = dstAddr;
1041  commStatus->status = status;
1042  commStatus->securityLevel = securityLevel;
1043  commStatus->keyIdMode = keyIdMode;
1044  commStatus->keyIndex = keyIndex;
1045 
1046  uint8_t n;
1047 
1048  if (securityLevel != 0)
1049  {
1050  if (keyIdMode == 0x2)
1051  {
1052  for (n = 0; n < 4; n++)
1053  {
1054  commStatus->keySource[ n ] = keySource[ n ];
1055  }
1056  }
1057  else if (keyIdMode == 0x3)
1058  {
1059  for (n = 0; n < 8; n++)
1060  {
1061  commStatus->keySource[ n ] = keySource[ n ];
1062  }
1063  }
1064  }
1065 
1066 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
1067 
1068  if (request &&
1069  (request->msgId == FTDF_ORPHAN_RESPONSE ||
1070  request->msgId == FTDF_ASSOCIATE_RESPONSE))
1071  {
1072  if (FTDF_reqCurrent == request)
1073  {
1074  FTDF_reqCurrent = NULL;
1075  }
1076 
1077  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER(request);
1078  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) commStatus);
1079  /* Check for orphan response. */
1080 #if FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO
1081  FTDF_fpFsmClearPending();
1082 #endif /* FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO */
1083  FTDF_processNextRequest();
1084  return;
1085  }
1086 
1087 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
1088  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) commStatus);
1089 }
1090 #endif /* FTDF_PHY_API */
1091 
1092 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
1093 FTDF_Octet *FTDF_addFrameHeader(FTDF_Octet *txPtr,
1094  FTDF_FrameHeader *frameHeader,
1095  FTDF_DataLength msduLength)
1096 {
1097  uint8_t frameVersion;
1098  uint8_t longFrameControl = 0x00;
1099  FTDF_Boolean panIdCompression = FTDF_FALSE;
1100  FTDF_Bitmap8 options = frameHeader->options;
1101  FTDF_Boolean secure = options & FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED;
1102  FTDF_Boolean framePending = options & FTDF_OPT_FRAME_PENDING;
1103  FTDF_Boolean ackTX = options & FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED;
1104  FTDF_Boolean panIdPresent = options & FTDF_OPT_PAN_ID_PRESENT;
1105  FTDF_Boolean seqNrSuppressed = options & FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED;
1106  FTDF_Boolean iesIncluded = options & FTDF_OPT_IES_PRESENT;
1107  FTDF_FrameType frameType = frameHeader->frameType;
1108  FTDF_AddressMode dstAddrMode = frameHeader->dstAddrMode;
1109  FTDF_AddressMode srcAddrMode = frameHeader->srcAddrMode;
1110  FTDF_PANId dstPANId = frameHeader->dstPANId;
1111 
1112  if (frameType == FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1113  {
1114  if (options & (FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED | FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED | FTDF_OPT_PAN_ID_PRESENT |
1115  FTDF_OPT_IES_PRESENT | FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED | FTDF_OPT_FRAME_PENDING))
1116  {
1117  longFrameControl = 0x08;
1118  }
1119 
1120  // Frame control field byte 1
1121  *txPtr++ = 0x05 | longFrameControl | dstAddrMode << 4 | srcAddrMode << 6;
1122 
1123  if (longFrameControl)
1124  {
1125  // Frame control field byte 2
1126  *txPtr++ =
1127  (panIdPresent ? 0x01 : 0x00) |
1128  (secure ? 0x02 : 0x00) |
1129  (seqNrSuppressed ? 0x04 : 0x00) |
1130  (framePending ? 0x08 : 0x00) |
1131  (ackTX ? 0x40 : 0x00) |
1132  (iesIncluded ? 0x80 : 0x00);
1133  }
1134  }
1135  else
1136  {
1137  // if ( panIdPresent || iesIncluded || seqNrSuppressed || ( options & FTDF_OPT_ENHANCED ) || FTDF_pib.tschEnabled )
1138  if (panIdPresent || iesIncluded || seqNrSuppressed || (options & FTDF_OPT_ENHANCED))
1139  {
1140  frameVersion = 0b10;
1141  }
1142  else
1143  {
1144  if (secure ||
1145  msduLength > FTDF_MAX_MAC_SAFE_PAYLOAD_SIZE)
1146  {
1147  frameVersion = 0b01;
1148  }
1149  else
1150  {
1151  frameVersion = 0b00;
1152  }
1153  }
1154 
1155  if (frameVersion < 0b10)
1156  {
1157  if (dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS &&
1158  srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS &&
1159  dstPANId == frameHeader->srcPANId)
1160  {
1161  panIdCompression = FTDF_TRUE;
1162  }
1163  }
1164  else
1165  {
1166  panIdCompression = panIdPresent;
1167  }
1168 
1169  // Frame control field byte 1
1170  *txPtr++ =
1171  (frameType & 0x7) |
1172  (secure ? 0x08 : 0x00) |
1173  (framePending ? 0x10 : 0x00) |
1174  (ackTX ? 0x20 : 0x00) |
1175  (panIdCompression ? 0x40 : 0x00);
1176 
1177  // Frame control field byte 2
1178  *txPtr++ =
1179  (seqNrSuppressed ? 0x01 : 0x00) |
1180  (iesIncluded ? 0x02 : 0x00) |
1181  dstAddrMode << 2 |
1182  frameVersion << 4 |
1183  srcAddrMode << 6;
1184  }
1185 
1186  if (!seqNrSuppressed)
1187  {
1188  *txPtr++ = frameHeader->SN;
1189  }
1190 
1191  FTDF_Boolean addDstPANId = FTDF_FALSE;
1192 
1193  if (frameType == FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1194  {
1195  if (panIdPresent)
1196  {
1197  addDstPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1198  }
1199  }
1200  else
1201  {
1202  if (frameVersion < 0b10)
1203  {
1204  if (dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS)
1205  {
1206  addDstPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1207  }
1208  }
1209  else
1210  {
1211  // See Table 2a "PAN ID Compression" of IEEE 802.15.4-2011 for more details
1212  if ((srcAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && panIdCompression) ||
1213  (srcAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression) ||
1214  (srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression))
1215  {
1216  addDstPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1217  }
1218  }
1219  }
1220 
1221  if (addDstPANId)
1222  {
1223  FTDF_Octet *PANIdPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&dstPANId;
1224 
1225  *txPtr++ = *PANIdPtr++;
1226  *txPtr++ = *PANIdPtr;
1227  }
1228 
1229  FTDF_Address dstAddr = frameHeader->dstAddr;
1230 
1231  if (dstAddrMode == FTDF_SIMPLE_ADDRESS)
1232  {
1233  *txPtr++ = dstAddr.simpleAddress;
1234  }
1235  else if (dstAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
1236  {
1237  FTDF_Octet *shortAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&dstAddr.shortAddress;
1238 
1239  *txPtr++ = *shortAddressPtr++;
1240  *txPtr++ = *shortAddressPtr;
1241  }
1242  else if (dstAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
1243  {
1244  FTDF_Octet *extAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&dstAddr.extAddress;
1245  int n;
1246 
1247  for (n = 0; n < 8; n++)
1248  {
1249  *txPtr++ = *extAddressPtr++;
1250  }
1251  }
1252 
1253  FTDF_Boolean addSrcPANId = FTDF_FALSE;
1254 
1255  if (frameType != FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1256  {
1257  if (frameVersion < 0b10)
1258  {
1259  if (srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression)
1260  {
1261  addSrcPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1262  }
1263  }
1264  else
1265  {
1266  // See Table 2a "PAN ID Compression" of IEEE 802.15.4-2011 for more details
1267  if (srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression)
1268  {
1269  addSrcPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1270  }
1271  }
1272  }
1273 
1274  if (addSrcPANId)
1275  {
1276  FTDF_Octet *PANIdPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&frameHeader->srcPANId;
1277 
1278  *txPtr++ = *PANIdPtr++;
1279  *txPtr++ = *PANIdPtr;
1280  }
1281 
1282  if (srcAddrMode == FTDF_SIMPLE_ADDRESS)
1283  {
1284  *txPtr++ = FTDF_pib.simpleAddress;
1285  }
1286  else if (srcAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
1287  {
1288  FTDF_Octet *shortAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&FTDF_pib.shortAddress;
1289 
1290  *txPtr++ = *shortAddressPtr++;
1291  *txPtr++ = *shortAddressPtr;
1292  }
1293  else if (srcAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
1294  {
1295  FTDF_Octet *extAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&FTDF_pib.extAddress;
1296  int n;
1297 
1298  for (n = 0; n < 8; n++)
1299  {
1300  *txPtr++ = *extAddressPtr++;
1301  }
1302  }
1303 
1304  return txPtr;
1305 }
1306 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
1307 
1308 FTDF_PTI FTDF_getRxPti(void)
1309 {
1310 #if FTDF_USE_PTI
1311  FTDF_PTI rx_pti;
1312  FTDF_criticalVar();
1313  FTDF_enterCritical();
1314  rx_pti = FTDF_RxPti;
1315  FTDF_exitCritical();
1316  return rx_pti;
1317 #else
1318  return 0;
1319 #endif
1320 }
1321 
1322 #ifdef FTDF_PHY_API
1323 void FTDF_rxEnable(FTDF_Time rxOnDuration)
1324 {
1325 #if dg_configCOEX_ENABLE_CONFIG
1326  /* We do not force decision here. It will be automatically made when FTDF begins
1327  * transaction.
1328  */
1329  hw_coex_update_ftdf_pti((hw_coex_pti_t) FTDF_getRxPti(), NULL, false);
1330 #endif
1331  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXENABLE, 0);
1332  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXONDURATION, rxOnDuration);
1333  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXENABLE, 1);
1334 }
1335 #else
1336 void FTDF_processRxEnableRequest(FTDF_RxEnableRequest *rxEnableRequest)
1337 {
1338  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXENABLE, 0);
1339  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXONDURATION, rxEnableRequest->rxOnDuration);
1340  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXENABLE, 1);
1341 
1342  FTDF_RxEnableConfirm *rxEnableConfirm =
1343  (FTDF_RxEnableConfirm *) FTDF_GET_MSG_BUFFER(sizeof(FTDF_RxEnableConfirm));
1344 
1345  rxEnableConfirm->msgId = FTDF_RX_ENABLE_CONFIRM;
1346  rxEnableConfirm->status = FTDF_SUCCESS;
1347 
1348  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) rxEnableRequest);
1349  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) rxEnableConfirm);
1350 }
1351 #endif /* FTDF_PHY_API */
1352 
1353 FTDF_Octet *FTDF_getFrameHeader(FTDF_Octet *rxBuffer,
1354  FTDF_FrameHeader *frameHeader)
1355 {
1356  FTDF_FrameType frameType = *rxBuffer & 0x07;
1357  uint8_t frameVersion = 0;
1358  FTDF_Bitmap8 options = 0;
1359  FTDF_AddressMode dstAddrMode;
1360  FTDF_AddressMode srcAddrMode;
1361  FTDF_Boolean panIdCompression = FTDF_FALSE;
1362  FTDF_Boolean panIdPresent = FTDF_FALSE;
1363 
1364  if (frameType == FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1365  {
1366  dstAddrMode = (*rxBuffer & 0x30) >> 4;
1367  srcAddrMode = (*rxBuffer & 0xc0) >> 6;
1368 
1369  // Check Long Frame Control
1370  if (*rxBuffer & 0x08)
1371  {
1372  rxBuffer++;
1373 
1374  panIdPresent = *rxBuffer & 0x01;
1375 
1376  if (*rxBuffer & 0x02)
1377  {
1378  options |= FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED;
1379  }
1380 
1381  if (*rxBuffer & 0x04)
1382  {
1383  options |= FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED;
1384  }
1385 
1386  if (*rxBuffer & 0x08)
1387  {
1388  options |= FTDF_OPT_FRAME_PENDING;
1389  }
1390 
1391  if (*rxBuffer & 0x40)
1392  {
1393  options |= FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED;
1394  }
1395 
1396  if (*rxBuffer & 0x80)
1397  {
1398  options |= FTDF_OPT_IES_PRESENT;
1399  }
1400 
1401  frameVersion = 0;
1402 
1403  frameHeader->frameVersion = FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E;
1404 
1405  rxBuffer++;
1406  }
1407  else
1408  {
1409  rxBuffer++;
1410  }
1411  }
1412  else
1413  {
1414  if (*rxBuffer & 0x08)
1415  {
1416  options |= FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED;
1417  }
1418 
1419  if (*rxBuffer & 0x10)
1420  {
1421  options |= FTDF_OPT_FRAME_PENDING;
1422  }
1423 
1424  if (*rxBuffer & 0x20)
1425  {
1426  options |= FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED;
1427  }
1428 
1429  panIdCompression = *rxBuffer & 0x40;
1430 
1431  rxBuffer++;
1432 
1433  frameVersion = (*rxBuffer & 0x30) >> 4;
1434 
1435  if (frameVersion == 0x02)
1436  {
1437  if (*rxBuffer & 0x01)
1438  {
1439  options |= FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED;
1440  }
1441 
1442  if (*rxBuffer & 0x02)
1443  {
1444  options |= FTDF_OPT_IES_PRESENT;
1445  }
1446 
1447  frameHeader->frameVersion = FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E;
1448  }
1449  else if (frameVersion == 0x01)
1450  {
1451  frameHeader->frameVersion = FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_2011;
1452  }
1453  else if (frameVersion == 0x00)
1454  {
1455  frameHeader->frameVersion = FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_2003;
1456  }
1457  else
1458  {
1459  frameHeader->frameVersion = FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED;
1460  return rxBuffer;
1461  }
1462 
1463  dstAddrMode = (*rxBuffer & 0x0c) >> 2;
1464  srcAddrMode = (*rxBuffer & 0xc0) >> 6;
1465 
1466  rxBuffer++;
1467  }
1468 
1469  if ((options & FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED) == 0)
1470  {
1471  frameHeader->SN = *rxBuffer++;
1472  }
1473 
1474  FTDF_Boolean hasDstPANId = FTDF_FALSE;
1475 
1476  if (frameType == FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1477  {
1478  hasDstPANId = panIdPresent;
1479  }
1480  else
1481  {
1482  if (frameVersion < 0x02)
1483  {
1484  if (dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS)
1485  {
1486  hasDstPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1487  }
1488  }
1489  else
1490  {
1491  if ((srcAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && panIdCompression) ||
1492  (srcAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression) ||
1493  (srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression))
1494  {
1495  hasDstPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1496  }
1497  }
1498  }
1499 
1500  if (hasDstPANId)
1501  {
1502  FTDF_Octet *PANIdPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) &frameHeader->dstPANId;
1503 
1504  *PANIdPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
1505  *PANIdPtr = *rxBuffer++;
1506  }
1507 
1508  if (dstAddrMode == FTDF_SIMPLE_ADDRESS)
1509  {
1510  frameHeader->dstAddr.simpleAddress = *rxBuffer++;
1511  }
1512  else if (dstAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
1513  {
1514  FTDF_Octet *shortAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&frameHeader->dstAddr.shortAddress;
1515 
1516  *shortAddressPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
1517  *shortAddressPtr = *rxBuffer++;
1518  }
1519  else if (dstAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
1520  {
1521  FTDF_Octet *extAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&frameHeader->dstAddr.extAddress;
1522  int n;
1523 
1524  for (n = 0; n < 8; n++)
1525  {
1526  *extAddressPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
1527  }
1528  }
1529 
1530  FTDF_Boolean hasSrcPANId = FTDF_FALSE;
1531 
1532  if (frameVersion < 0x02 && frameType != FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1533  {
1534  if (srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression)
1535  {
1536  hasSrcPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1537  }
1538  }
1539  else
1540  {
1541  if (srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && dstAddrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS && !panIdCompression)
1542  {
1543  hasSrcPANId = FTDF_TRUE;
1544  }
1545  }
1546 
1547  if (hasSrcPANId)
1548  {
1549  FTDF_Octet *PANIdPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) &frameHeader->srcPANId;
1550 
1551  *PANIdPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
1552  *PANIdPtr = *rxBuffer++;
1553  }
1554  else
1555  {
1556  frameHeader->srcPANId = frameHeader->dstPANId;
1557  }
1558 
1559  if (srcAddrMode == FTDF_SIMPLE_ADDRESS)
1560  {
1561  frameHeader->srcAddr.simpleAddress = *rxBuffer++;
1562  }
1563  else if (srcAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
1564  {
1565  FTDF_Octet *shortAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&frameHeader->srcAddr.shortAddress;
1566 
1567  *shortAddressPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
1568  *shortAddressPtr = *rxBuffer++;
1569  }
1570  else if (srcAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
1571  {
1572  FTDF_Octet *extAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&frameHeader->srcAddr.extAddress;
1573  int n;
1574 
1575  for (n = 0; n < 8; n++)
1576  {
1577  *extAddressPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
1578  }
1579  }
1580 
1581  frameHeader->frameType = frameType;
1582  frameHeader->options = options;
1583  frameHeader->dstAddrMode = dstAddrMode;
1584  frameHeader->srcAddrMode = srcAddrMode;
1585 
1586  return rxBuffer;
1587 }
1588 
1589 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
1590 void FTDF_processNextRequest(void)
1591 {
1592 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
1593 
1594  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
1595  {
1596  FTDF_MsgBuffer *request = FTDF_tschGetPending(FTDF_tschSlotLink->request);
1597 
1598  FTDF_tschSlotLink->request = NULL;
1599 
1600  FTDF_scheduleTsch(request);
1601 
1602  return;
1603  }
1604 
1605 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
1606 
1607  while (FTDF_reqCurrent == NULL)
1608  {
1609  FTDF_MsgBuffer *request = FTDF_dequeueReqTail(&FTDF_reqQueue);
1610 
1611  if (request)
1612  {
1613  FTDF_processRequest(request);
1614  }
1615  else
1616  {
1617  break;
1618  }
1619  }
1620 }
1621 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
1622 
1623 static void processRxFrame(int readBuf)
1624 {
1625  static FTDF_PANDescriptor PANDescriptor;
1626  static FTDF_Address pendAddrList[ 7 ];
1627 
1628  FTDF_FrameHeader *frameHeader = &FTDF_fh;
1629 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
1630  FTDF_SecurityHeader *securityHeader = &FTDF_sh;
1631 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
1632 
1633  uint8_t pendAddrSpec = 0;
1634 
1635  FTDF_Octet *rxBuffer =
1636  (FTDF_Octet *)(IND_R_FTDF_RX_RAM_RX_FIFO + (intptr_t) readBuf * FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH);
1637  FTDF_Octet *rxPtr = rxBuffer;
1638  FTDF_DataLength frameLen = *rxPtr++;
1639 
1640  if (FTDF_transparentMode)
1641  {
1642  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
1643  {
1644  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.RXSuccessCount++;
1645  }
1646 
1647  uint32_t rxMeta1 = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_META_1, (intptr_t)readBuf);
1648  FTDF_LinkQuality lqi = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_QUALITY_INDICATOR, readBuf);
1649  FTDF_Bitmap32 status = FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_SUCCESSFUL;
1650 
1651  status |= rxMeta1 & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CRC16_ERROR ? FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_CRC_ERROR : 0;
1652  status |= rxMeta1 & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_RES_FRM_TYPE_ERROR ? FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_RES_FRAMETYPE : 0;
1653  status |= rxMeta1 & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_RES_FRM_VERSION_ERROR ? FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_RES_FRAME_VERSION : 0;
1654  status |= rxMeta1 & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_DPANID_ERROR ? FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_UNEXP_DST_PAN_ID : 0;
1655  status |= rxMeta1 & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_DADDR_ERROR ? FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_UNEXP_DST_ADDR : 0;
1656 
1657  FTDF_RCV_FRAME_TRANSPARENT(frameLen, rxPtr, status, lqi);
1658 
1659 #if FTDF_TRANSPARENT_USE_WAIT_FOR_ACK
1660 
1661  if ((FTDF_transparentModeOptions & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_WAIT_FOR_ACK))
1662  {
1663  FTDF_getFrameHeader(rxPtr, frameHeader);
1664 
1665  if (frameHeader->frameType == FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME &&
1666  (status == FTDF_TRANSPARENT_RCV_SUCCESSFUL))
1667  {
1668 
1669 #ifndef FTDF_PHY_API
1670  volatile uint32_t *txFlagS = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_S, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
1671 
1672  while (*txFlagS & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_STAT)
1673  { }
1674 
1675  // It is required to call FTDF_processTxEvent here because an RX ack generates two events
1676  // The RX event is raised first, then after an IFS the TX event is raised. However,
1677  // the FTDF_processNextRequest requires that both events have been handled.
1678  FTDF_processTxEvent();
1679 #endif /* !FTDF_PHY_API */
1680 
1681  FTDF_SN SN = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_MACSN, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
1682 
1683 #ifdef FTDF_PHY_API
1684  FTDF_criticalVar();
1685  FTDF_enterCritical();
1686 
1687  if (FTDF_txInProgress &&
1688  frameHeader->SN == SN)
1689  {
1690  FTDF_exitCritical();
1691  return;
1692  }
1693 
1694  FTDF_exitCritical();
1695 #else
1696 
1697  if (FTDF_reqCurrent &&
1698  frameHeader->SN == SN)
1699  {
1700  FTDF_TransparentRequest *transparentRequest = (FTDF_TransparentRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
1701 
1702  FTDF_criticalVar();
1703  FTDF_enterCritical();
1704  FTDF_reqCurrent = NULL;
1705  FTDF_exitCritical();
1706  FTDF_SEND_FRAME_TRANSPARENT_CONFIRM(transparentRequest->handle, FTDF_TRANSPARENT_SEND_SUCCESSFUL);
1707 
1708  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) transparentRequest);
1709 
1710  return;
1711  }
1712 
1713 #endif /* FTDF_PHY_API */
1714  }
1715  }
1716 
1717 #endif /* FTDF_TRANSPARENT_USE_WAIT_FOR_ACK */
1718  return;
1719  }
1720 
1721 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
1722  rxPtr = FTDF_getFrameHeader(rxPtr, frameHeader);
1723 
1724 #if FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_MANUAL
1725 
1726  if (frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED)
1727  {
1728  int n;
1729  FTDF_Boolean addressFound = FTDF_FALSE;
1730 
1731  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_REQ_BUFFERS; n++)
1732  {
1733  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addrMode == frameHeader->srcAddrMode &&
1734  FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].PANId == frameHeader->srcPANId)
1735  {
1736  if (frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
1737  {
1738  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addr.shortAddress ==
1739  frameHeader->srcAddr.shortAddress)
1740  {
1741  addressFound = FTDF_TRUE;
1742  break;
1743  }
1744  }
1745  else if (frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
1746  {
1747  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addr.extAddress ==
1748  frameHeader->srcAddr.extAddress)
1749  {
1750  addressFound = FTDF_TRUE;
1751  break;
1752  }
1753  }
1754  else
1755  {
1756  // Invalid srcAddrMode
1757  return;
1758  }
1759  }
1760  }
1761 
1762  if (addressFound)
1763  {
1764  FTDF_fpprSetMode(FTDF_FALSE, FTDF_TRUE, FTDF_TRUE);
1765  }
1766  else
1767  {
1768  FTDF_fpprSetMode(FTDF_FALSE, FTDF_TRUE, FTDF_FALSE);
1769  }
1770  }
1771 
1772 #endif
1773 
1774  if (frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED)
1775  {
1776  return;
1777  }
1778 
1779 #if defined(FTDF_NO_CSL) && defined(FTDF_NO_TSCH)
1780  else if (frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E ||
1781  frameHeader->frameType == FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
1782  {
1783  return;
1784  }
1785 
1786 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL && FTDF_NO_TSCH */
1787 
1788  FTDF_FrameType frameType = frameHeader->frameType;
1789  FTDF_Boolean duplicate = FTDF_FALSE;
1790 
1791  if ((frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED) == 0 &&
1792  frameHeader->srcAddrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS)
1793  {
1794  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP, readBuf);
1795  FTDF_SNSel snSel = FTDF_SN_SEL_DSN;
1796  FTDF_Boolean drop;
1797 
1798  if ((FTDF_pib.tschEnabled || frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E) &&
1799  (frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED))
1800  {
1801  drop = FTDF_FALSE;
1802  }
1803  else
1804  {
1805  drop = FTDF_TRUE;
1806  }
1807 
1808  if (frameType == FTDF_BEACON_FRAME)
1809  {
1810  snSel = frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E ? FTDF_SN_SEL_EBSN : FTDF_SN_SEL_BSN;
1811  }
1812 
1813  uint8_t i;
1814 
1815  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_NR_OF_RX_ADDRS; i++)
1816  {
1817  // Check if entry is empty or matches
1818  if (FTDF_rxa[ i ].addrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS ||
1819  (FTDF_rxa[ i ].addrMode == frameHeader->srcAddrMode &&
1820  ((frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS &&
1821  frameHeader->srcAddr.shortAddress == FTDF_rxa[ i ].addr.shortAddress) ||
1822  (frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS &&
1823  frameHeader->srcAddr.extAddress == FTDF_rxa[ i ].addr.extAddress))))
1824  {
1825  break;
1826  }
1827  }
1828 
1829  if (i < FTDF_NR_OF_RX_ADDRS)
1830  {
1831  if (FTDF_rxa[ i ].addrMode != FTDF_NO_ADDRESS)
1832  {
1833  switch (snSel)
1834  {
1835  case FTDF_SN_SEL_DSN:
1836 
1837  if (FTDF_rxa[ i ].dsnValid == FTDF_TRUE)
1838  {
1839  if (frameHeader->SN == FTDF_rxa[ i ].dsn)
1840  {
1841  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
1842  {
1843  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.duplicateFrameCount++;
1844  }
1845 
1846  if (drop)
1847  {
1848  return;
1849  }
1850 
1851  duplicate = FTDF_TRUE;
1852  }
1853  }
1854  else
1855  {
1856  FTDF_rxa[ i ].dsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1857  }
1858 
1859  FTDF_rxa[ i ].dsn = frameHeader->SN;
1860  break;
1861 
1862  case FTDF_SN_SEL_BSN:
1863 
1864  if (FTDF_rxa[ i ].bsnValid == FTDF_TRUE)
1865  {
1866  if (frameHeader->SN == FTDF_rxa[ i ].bsn)
1867  {
1868  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
1869  {
1870  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.duplicateFrameCount++;
1871  }
1872 
1873  if (drop)
1874  {
1875  return;
1876  }
1877 
1878  duplicate = FTDF_TRUE;
1879  }
1880  }
1881  else
1882  {
1883  FTDF_rxa[ i ].bsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1884  }
1885 
1886  FTDF_rxa[ i ].bsn = frameHeader->SN;
1887  break;
1888 
1889  case FTDF_SN_SEL_EBSN:
1890 
1891  if (FTDF_rxa[ i ].ebsnValid == FTDF_TRUE)
1892  {
1893  if (frameHeader->SN == FTDF_rxa[ i ].ebsn)
1894  {
1895  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
1896  {
1897  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.duplicateFrameCount++;
1898  }
1899 
1900  if (drop)
1901  {
1902  return;
1903  }
1904 
1905  duplicate = FTDF_TRUE;
1906  }
1907  }
1908  else
1909  {
1910  FTDF_rxa[ i ].ebsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1911  }
1912 
1913  FTDF_rxa[ i ].ebsn = frameHeader->SN;
1914  break;
1915  }
1916  }
1917  else
1918  {
1919  FTDF_rxa[ i ].addrMode = frameHeader->srcAddrMode;
1920  FTDF_rxa[ i ].addr = frameHeader->srcAddr;
1921 
1922  switch (snSel)
1923  {
1924  case FTDF_SN_SEL_DSN:
1925  FTDF_rxa[ i ].dsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1926  FTDF_rxa[ i ].dsn = frameHeader->SN;
1927  break;
1928 
1929  case FTDF_SN_SEL_BSN:
1930  FTDF_rxa[ i ].bsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1931  FTDF_rxa[ i ].bsn = frameHeader->SN;
1932  break;
1933 
1934  case FTDF_SN_SEL_EBSN:
1935  FTDF_rxa[ i ].ebsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1936  FTDF_rxa[ i ].ebsn = frameHeader->SN;
1937  break;
1938  }
1939  }
1940 
1941  FTDF_rxa[ i ].timestamp = timestamp;
1942  }
1943  else
1944  {
1945  // find oldest entry and overwrite it
1946  FTDF_Time curTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
1947  FTDF_Time delta, greatestDelta = 0;
1948  uint8_t entry = 0;
1949 
1950  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_NR_OF_RX_ADDRS; i++)
1951  {
1952  delta = curTime - FTDF_rxa[ i ].timestamp;
1953 
1954  if (delta > greatestDelta)
1955  {
1956  greatestDelta = delta;
1957  entry = i;
1958  }
1959  }
1960 
1961  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].addrMode = frameHeader->srcAddrMode;
1962  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].addr = frameHeader->srcAddr;
1963 
1964  switch (snSel)
1965  {
1966  case FTDF_SN_SEL_DSN:
1967  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].bsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
1968  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].ebsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
1969  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].dsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1970  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].dsn = frameHeader->SN;
1971  break;
1972 
1973  case FTDF_SN_SEL_BSN:
1974  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].dsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
1975  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].ebsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
1976  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].bsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1977  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].bsn = frameHeader->SN;
1978  break;
1979 
1980  case FTDF_SN_SEL_EBSN:
1981  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].dsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
1982  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].bsnValid = FTDF_FALSE;
1983  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].ebsnValid = FTDF_TRUE;
1984  FTDF_rxa[ entry ].ebsn = frameHeader->SN;
1985  break;
1986  }
1987  }
1988  }
1989 
1990  if (frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED)
1991  {
1992  rxPtr = FTDF_getSecurityHeader(rxPtr, frameHeader->frameVersion, securityHeader);
1993  }
1994  else
1995  {
1996  securityHeader->securityLevel = 0;
1997  securityHeader->keyIdMode = 0;
1998  }
1999 
2000  FTDF_IEList *headerIEList = NULL;
2001  FTDF_IEList *payloadIEList = NULL;
2002  int micLength = FTDF_getMicLength(securityHeader->securityLevel);
2003 
2004 #if !defined(FTDF_NO_CSL) || !defined(FTDF_NO_TSCH)
2005 
2006  if (frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_IES_PRESENT)
2007  {
2008  rxPtr =
2009  FTDF_getIes(rxPtr, rxBuffer + (frameLen - micLength - FTDF_FCS_LENGTH), &headerIEList, &payloadIEList);
2010  }
2011 
2012 #endif /* !FTDF_NO_CSL || !FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2013 
2014  // Get start of private data (needed to unsecure a frame)
2015  if (frameType == FTDF_MAC_COMMAND_FRAME)
2016  {
2017  frameHeader->commandFrameId = *rxPtr++;
2018  }
2019  else if (frameType == FTDF_BEACON_FRAME)
2020  {
2021  PANDescriptor.coordAddrMode = frameHeader->srcAddrMode;
2022  PANDescriptor.coordPANId = frameHeader->srcPANId;
2023  PANDescriptor.coordAddr = frameHeader->srcAddr;
2024  PANDescriptor.channelNumber = ((FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYRXATTR) >> 4) & 0xf) + 11;
2025  PANDescriptor.channelPage = 0;
2026  PANDescriptor.timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP, readBuf);
2027  PANDescriptor.linkQuality = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_QUALITY_INDICATOR, readBuf);
2028 
2029  FTDF_Octet *superframeSpecPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) &PANDescriptor.superframeSpec;
2030  *superframeSpecPtr++ = *rxPtr++;
2031  *superframeSpecPtr = *rxPtr++;
2032 
2033  uint8_t gtsSpec = *rxPtr++;
2034 
2035  PANDescriptor.GTSPermit = (gtsSpec & 0x08) ? FTDF_TRUE : FTDF_FALSE;
2036  uint8_t gtsDescrCount = gtsSpec & 0x7;
2037 
2038  if (gtsDescrCount != 0)
2039  {
2040  // GTS is not supported, so just skip the GTS direction and GTS list fields if present
2041  rxPtr += (1 + (3 * gtsDescrCount));
2042  }
2043 
2044  pendAddrSpec = *rxPtr++;
2045  uint8_t nrOfShortAddrs = pendAddrSpec & 0x07;
2046  uint8_t nrOfExtAddrs = (pendAddrSpec & 0x70) >> 4;
2047 
2048  int n;
2049 
2050  for (n = 0; n < (nrOfShortAddrs + nrOfExtAddrs); n++)
2051  {
2052  if (n < nrOfShortAddrs)
2053  {
2054  FTDF_Octet *shortAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) &pendAddrList[ n ].shortAddress;
2055  *shortAddressPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
2056  *shortAddressPtr = *rxBuffer++;
2057  }
2058  else
2059  {
2060  FTDF_Octet *extAddressPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) &pendAddrList[ n ].extAddress;
2061  int m;
2062 
2063  for (m = 0; m < 8; m++)
2064  {
2065  *extAddressPtr++ = *rxBuffer++;
2066  }
2067  }
2068  }
2069  }
2070  else if (frameType == FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME &&
2071  securityHeader->securityLevel != 0)
2072  {
2073  if (FTDF_reqCurrent)
2074  {
2075  switch (FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId)
2076  {
2077  case FTDF_DATA_REQUEST:
2078  {
2079  FTDF_DataRequest *dataRequest = (FTDF_DataRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2080  frameHeader->srcPANId = dataRequest->dstPANId;
2081  frameHeader->srcAddrMode = dataRequest->dstAddrMode;
2082  frameHeader->srcAddr = dataRequest->dstAddr;
2083  break;
2084  }
2085 
2086  case FTDF_POLL_REQUEST:
2087  {
2088  FTDF_PollRequest *pollRequest = (FTDF_PollRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2089  frameHeader->srcPANId = pollRequest->coordPANId;
2090  frameHeader->srcAddrMode = pollRequest->coordAddrMode;
2091  frameHeader->srcAddr = pollRequest->coordAddr;
2092  break;
2093  }
2094 
2095  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
2096  {
2097  FTDF_AssociateRequest *associateRequest = (FTDF_AssociateRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2098  frameHeader->srcPANId = associateRequest->coordPANId;
2099  frameHeader->srcAddrMode = associateRequest->coordAddrMode;
2100  frameHeader->srcAddr = associateRequest->coordAddr;
2101  break;
2102  }
2103 
2104  case FTDF_DISASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
2105  {
2106  FTDF_DisassociateRequest *disassociateRequest =
2107  (FTDF_DisassociateRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2108  frameHeader->srcPANId = disassociateRequest->devicePANId;
2109  frameHeader->srcAddrMode = disassociateRequest->deviceAddrMode;
2110  frameHeader->srcAddr = disassociateRequest->deviceAddress;
2111  break;
2112  }
2113 
2114  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_RESPONSE:
2115  {
2116  FTDF_AssociateResponse *associateResponse = (FTDF_AssociateResponse *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2117  frameHeader->srcAddrMode = FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS;
2118  frameHeader->srcAddr.extAddress = associateResponse->deviceAddress;
2119  break;
2120  }
2121  }
2122  }
2123  }
2124 
2125  FTDF_Status status = FTDF_unsecureFrame(rxBuffer, rxPtr, frameHeader, securityHeader);
2126 
2127  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2128  {
2129  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
2130  {
2131  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.securityFailureCount++;
2132  }
2133 
2134  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2135 
2136  // Since unsecure of acknowledgement frame is always successful,
2137  // nothing special has to be done to get the address information correct.
2138  FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(FTDF_reqCurrent, status,
2139  FTDF_pib.PANId,
2140  frameHeader->srcAddrMode,
2141  frameHeader->srcAddr,
2142  frameHeader->dstAddrMode,
2143  frameHeader->dstAddr,
2144  securityHeader->securityLevel,
2145  securityHeader->keyIdMode,
2146  securityHeader->keySource,
2147  securityHeader->keyIndex);
2148 
2149  if (frameType == FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME && FTDF_reqCurrent)
2150  {
2151  sendConfirm(FTDF_NO_ACK,
2152  FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId);
2153 
2154  FTDF_processNextRequest();
2155  }
2156 
2157  return;
2158  }
2159 
2160  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled && frameType != FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME)
2161  {
2162  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.RXSuccessCount++;
2163  }
2164 
2165 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
2166 
2167  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled && frameType != FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME)
2168  {
2169  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP, readBuf);
2170 
2171  FTDF_correctSlotTime(timestamp);
2172  }
2173 
2174 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2175 
2176  switch (frameType)
2177  {
2178  case FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME:
2179 
2180  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
2181  {
2182  if (FTDF_nrOfRetries == 0)
2183  {
2184  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.TXSuccessCount++;
2185  }
2186  else if (FTDF_nrOfRetries == 1)
2187  {
2188  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.retryCount++;
2189  }
2190  else
2191  {
2192  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.multipleRetryCount++;
2193  }
2194  }
2195 
2196  if (frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E)
2197  {
2198  FTDF_pib.trafficCounters.rxEnhAckFrmOkCnt++;
2199  }
2200 
2201  break;
2202 
2203  case FTDF_BEACON_FRAME:
2204  FTDF_pib.trafficCounters.rxBeaconFrmOkCnt++;
2205  break;
2206 
2207  case FTDF_DATA_FRAME:
2208  FTDF_pib.trafficCounters.rxDataFrmOkCnt++;
2209  break;
2210 
2211  case FTDF_MAC_COMMAND_FRAME:
2212  FTDF_pib.trafficCounters.rxCmdFrmOkCnt++;
2213  break;
2214 
2215  case FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME:
2216  FTDF_pib.trafficCounters.rxMultiPurpFrmOkCnt++;
2217  break;
2218  }
2219 
2220  if (frameType == FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME)
2221  {
2222  volatile uint32_t *txFlagS = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_S, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2223 
2224  while (*txFlagS & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_STAT)
2225  { }
2226 
2227  // It is required to call FTDF_processTxEvent here because an RX ack generates two events
2228  // The RX event is raised first, then after an IFS the TX event is raised. However,
2229  // the FTDF_processNextRequest requires that both events have been handled.
2230  FTDF_processTxEvent();
2231 
2232  FTDF_SN SN = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_MACSN, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2233 
2234  if (FTDF_reqCurrent &&
2235  frameHeader->SN == SN)
2236  {
2237 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
2238 
2239  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
2240  {
2241  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP,
2242  readBuf);
2243 
2244  FTDF_setPeerCslTiming(headerIEList, timestamp);
2245  }
2246 
2247 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
2248 
2249 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
2250 
2251  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
2252  {
2253  FTDF_correctSlotTimeFromAck(headerIEList);
2254 
2255  FTDF_TschRetry *tschRetry = FTDF_getTschRetry(FTDF_getRequestAddress(FTDF_reqCurrent));
2256 
2257  tschRetry->nrOfRetries = 0;
2258  FTDF_tschSlotLink->request = NULL;
2259  }
2260 
2261 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2262 
2263  switch (FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId)
2264  {
2265  case FTDF_DATA_REQUEST:
2266  {
2267  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TXTIMESTAMP,
2268  FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2269  FTDF_NumOfBackoffs numOfBackoffs = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_CSMACANRRETRIES,
2270  FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2271 
2272  FTDF_sendDataConfirm((FTDF_DataRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent,
2273  FTDF_SUCCESS,
2274  timestamp,
2275  SN,
2276  numOfBackoffs,
2277  payloadIEList);
2278 
2279  break;
2280  }
2281 
2282  case FTDF_POLL_REQUEST:
2283  {
2284  if (!(frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_FRAME_PENDING))
2285  {
2286  FTDF_sendPollConfirm((FTDF_PollRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, FTDF_NO_DATA);
2287  }
2288 
2289  break;
2290  }
2291 
2292  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
2293  {
2294  FTDF_AssocAdmin *assocAdmin = &FTDF_aa;
2295 
2296  if (assocAdmin->fastA == FTDF_TRUE ||
2297  assocAdmin->dataR == FTDF_FALSE)
2298  {
2299  uint32_t timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
2300  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIME2THR,
2301  (timestamp + FTDF_pib.responseWaitTime * FTDF_BASE_SUPERFRAME_DURATION));
2302  }
2303  else if (!(frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_FRAME_PENDING))
2304  {
2305  FTDF_sendAssociateConfirm((FTDF_AssociateRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent,
2306  FTDF_NO_DATA,
2307  0xffff);
2308  }
2309 
2310  break;
2311  }
2312 
2313  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_RESPONSE:
2314  {
2315  FTDF_AssociateResponse *assocResp = (FTDF_AssociateResponse *)FTDF_reqCurrent;
2316 
2317  FTDF_Address srcAddr, dstAddr;
2318  srcAddr.extAddress = FTDF_pib.extAddress;
2319  dstAddr.extAddress = assocResp->deviceAddress;
2320 
2321  FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(FTDF_reqCurrent, FTDF_SUCCESS,
2322  FTDF_pib.PANId,
2323  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2324  srcAddr,
2325  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2326  dstAddr,
2327  assocResp->securityLevel,
2328  assocResp->keyIdMode,
2329  assocResp->keySource,
2330  assocResp->keyIndex);
2331  break;
2332  }
2333 
2334  case FTDF_ORPHAN_RESPONSE:
2335  {
2336  FTDF_OrphanResponse *orphanResp = (FTDF_OrphanResponse *)FTDF_reqCurrent;
2337 
2338  FTDF_Address srcAddr, dstAddr;
2339  srcAddr.extAddress = FTDF_pib.extAddress;
2340  dstAddr.extAddress = orphanResp->orphanAddress;
2341 
2342  FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(FTDF_reqCurrent, FTDF_SUCCESS,
2343  FTDF_pib.PANId,
2344  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2345  srcAddr,
2346  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2347  dstAddr,
2348  orphanResp->securityLevel,
2349  orphanResp->keyIdMode,
2350  orphanResp->keySource,
2351  orphanResp->keyIndex);
2352  break;
2353  }
2354 
2355  case FTDF_DISASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
2356  {
2357  FTDF_sendDisassociateConfirm((FTDF_DisassociateRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, FTDF_SUCCESS);
2358  break;
2359  }
2360 
2361  case FTDF_REMOTE_REQUEST:
2362  {
2363  FTDF_RemoteRequest *remoteRequest = (FTDF_RemoteRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2364 
2365  if (remoteRequest->remoteId == FTDF_REMOTE_PAN_ID_CONFLICT_NOTIFICATION)
2366  {
2367  FTDF_sendSyncLossIndication(FTDF_PAN_ID_CONFLICT, securityHeader);
2368  }
2369 
2370  FTDF_reqCurrent = NULL;
2371 
2372  break;
2373  }
2374  }
2375 
2376  if (FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId != FTDF_DATA_REQUEST)
2377  {
2378  // for data request the application owns the memory
2379  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2380  }
2381 
2382  FTDF_processNextRequest();
2383  }
2384  else
2385  {
2386  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2387  }
2388  }
2389  else if ((frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E || FTDF_pib.tschEnabled) &&
2390  (frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED))
2391  {
2392 #if !defined(FTDF_NO_CSL) || !defined(FTDF_NO_TSCH)
2393  static FTDF_FrameHeader afh;
2394  FTDF_FrameHeader *ackFrameHeader = &afh;
2395 
2396  ackFrameHeader->frameType = FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME;
2397  ackFrameHeader->options =
2398  (frameHeader->options &
2399  (FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED | FTDF_OPT_SEQ_NR_SUPPRESSED)) | FTDF_OPT_ENHANCED;
2400 
2401  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled == FTDF_TRUE ||
2402  FTDF_pib.tschEnabled == FTDF_TRUE ||
2403  FTDF_pib.EAckIEList.nrOfIEs != 0)
2404  {
2405  ackFrameHeader->options |= FTDF_OPT_IES_PRESENT;
2406  }
2407 
2408  ackFrameHeader->dstAddrMode = FTDF_NO_ADDRESS;
2409  ackFrameHeader->srcAddrMode = FTDF_NO_ADDRESS;
2410  ackFrameHeader->SN = frameHeader->SN;
2411 
2412  FTDF_Octet *txPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_FIFO) +
2413  (FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH * FTDF_TX_ACK_BUFFER);
2414 
2415  // Skip PHY header (= MAC length)
2416  txPtr++;
2417 
2418  txPtr = FTDF_addFrameHeader(txPtr,
2419  ackFrameHeader,
2420  0);
2421 
2422  if (frameHeader->options & FTDF_OPT_SECURITY_ENABLED)
2423  {
2424  securityHeader->frameCounter = FTDF_pib.frameCounter;
2425  securityHeader->frameCounterMode = FTDF_pib.frameCounterMode;
2426 
2427  txPtr = FTDF_addSecurityHeader(txPtr,
2428  securityHeader);
2429  }
2430 
2431 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
2432 
2433  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
2434  {
2435  static FTDF_Octet phaseAndPeriod[ 4 ];
2436  static FTDF_IEDescriptor cslIE = { 0x1a, 4, { phaseAndPeriod } };
2437  static FTDF_IEList cslIEList = { 1, &cslIE };
2438  FTDF_Time curTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
2439 
2440  FTDF_Time delta = curTime -
2441  (FTDF_startCslSampleTime - FTDF_pib.CSLPeriod * 10);
2442 
2443  *(FTDF_Period *)(phaseAndPeriod + 0) = (FTDF_Period)(delta / 10);
2444  *(FTDF_Period *)(phaseAndPeriod + 2) = FTDF_pib.CSLPeriod;
2445 
2446  txPtr = FTDF_addIes(txPtr,
2447  &cslIEList,
2448  &FTDF_pib.EAckIEList,
2449  FTDF_FALSE);
2450  }
2451 
2452 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
2453 
2454 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
2455 
2456  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
2457  {
2458  FTDF_Time rxTimestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP, readBuf);
2459 
2460  txPtr = FTDF_addCorrTimeIE(txPtr, rxTimestamp);
2461  }
2462 
2463 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2464 
2465  if (!FTDF_pib.leEnabled && !FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
2466  {
2467  txPtr = FTDF_addIes(txPtr,
2468  NULL,
2469  &FTDF_pib.EAckIEList,
2470  FTDF_FALSE);
2471  }
2472 
2473  FTDF_sendAckFrame(frameHeader,
2474  securityHeader,
2475  txPtr);
2476 #endif /* !FTDF_NO_CSL || !FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2477 
2478  if (duplicate)
2479  {
2480  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2481  return;
2482  }
2483  }
2484 
2485  if (frameType == FTDF_DATA_FRAME || frameType == FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME)
2486  {
2487  FTDF_DataLength payloadLength = frameLen -
2488  (rxPtr - rxBuffer) + 1 - micLength - FTDF_FCS_LENGTH;
2489 
2490  if (FTDF_reqCurrent &&
2491  FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId == FTDF_POLL_REQUEST)
2492  {
2493  FTDF_PollRequest *pollRequest = (FTDF_PollRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2494 
2495  if (frameHeader->srcAddrMode == pollRequest->coordAddrMode &&
2496  frameHeader->srcPANId == pollRequest->coordPANId &&
2497  ((frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS &&
2498  frameHeader->srcAddr.shortAddress == pollRequest->coordAddr.shortAddress) ||
2499  (frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS &&
2500  frameHeader->srcAddr.extAddress == pollRequest->coordAddr.extAddress)))
2501  {
2502  if (payloadLength == 0)
2503  {
2504  FTDF_sendPollConfirm(pollRequest, FTDF_NO_DATA);
2505  }
2506  else
2507  {
2508  FTDF_sendPollConfirm(pollRequest, FTDF_SUCCESS);
2509  }
2510  }
2511  }
2512  else if (FTDF_reqCurrent &&
2513  FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId == FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST &&
2514  payloadLength == 0)
2515  {
2516  sendConfirm(FTDF_NO_DATA, FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST);
2517  }
2518 
2519  if (payloadLength != 0)
2520  {
2521  FTDF_LinkQuality mpduLinkQuality = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_QUALITY_INDICATOR,
2522  readBuf);
2523  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP,
2524  readBuf);
2525 
2526  FTDF_sendDataIndication(frameHeader,
2527  securityHeader,
2528  payloadIEList,
2529  payloadLength,
2530  rxPtr,
2531  mpduLinkQuality,
2532  timestamp);
2533  }
2534 
2535 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
2536  else if (headerIEList->nrOfIEs == 1 &&
2537  headerIEList->IEs[ 0 ].ID == 0x1d)
2538  {
2539  FTDF_Period rzTime = *(uint16_t *) headerIEList->IEs[ 0 ].content.raw;
2540 
2541  FTDF_criticalVar();
2542  FTDF_enterCritical();
2543 
2544  FTDF_Time curTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
2545 
2546  FTDF_rzTime = curTime + (FTDF_Time) rzTime * 10 + 260; // 260 length of max frame in symbols
2547 
2548  FTDF_Time CSLPeriod = FTDF_pib.CSLPeriod * 10;
2549  FTDF_Time delta = FTDF_rzTime - FTDF_startCslSampleTime;
2550 
2551  while (delta < 0x80000000) // A delta larger than 0x80000000 is assumed a negative delta
2552  {
2553  FTDF_startCslSampleTime += CSLPeriod;
2554  delta = FTDF_rzTime - FTDF_startCslSampleTime;
2555  }
2556 
2557  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACCSLSTARTSAMPLETIME, FTDF_startCslSampleTime);
2558 
2559  FTDF_exitCritical();
2560 
2561  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2562  }
2563 
2564 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
2565  else
2566  {
2567  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2568  }
2569  }
2570  else if (frameType == FTDF_MAC_COMMAND_FRAME)
2571  {
2572  FTDF_processCommandFrame(rxPtr, frameHeader, securityHeader, payloadIEList);
2573  }
2574  else if (frameType == FTDF_BEACON_FRAME)
2575  {
2576  FTDF_Octet *superframeSpecPtr = (FTDF_Octet *)&PANDescriptor.superframeSpec;
2577  superframeSpecPtr++;
2578 
2579  if (FTDF_isPANCoordinator)
2580  {
2581  if (frameHeader->srcPANId == FTDF_pib.PANId && (*superframeSpecPtr & 0x40))
2582  {
2583  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2584  FTDF_sendSyncLossIndication(FTDF_PAN_ID_CONFLICT, securityHeader);
2585  return;
2586  }
2587  }
2588  else if (FTDF_pib.associatedPANCoord)
2589  {
2590  if (frameHeader->srcPANId == FTDF_pib.PANId && (*superframeSpecPtr & 0x40) &&
2591  ((frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS &&
2592  frameHeader->srcAddr.shortAddress != FTDF_pib.coordShortAddress) ||
2593  (frameHeader->srcAddrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS &&
2594  frameHeader->srcAddr.extAddress != FTDF_pib.coordExtAddress)))
2595  {
2596  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2597  FTDF_sendPANIdConflictNotification(frameHeader, securityHeader);
2598  return;
2599  }
2600  }
2601 
2602  FTDF_DataLength beaconPayloadLength = frameLen - (rxPtr - rxBuffer) + 1 - micLength - FTDF_FCS_LENGTH;
2603 
2604  if (FTDF_pib.autoRequest == FTDF_FALSE ||
2605  beaconPayloadLength != 0)
2606  {
2607  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_RX_TIMESTAMP,
2608  readBuf);
2609 
2610  FTDF_BeaconNotifyIndication *beaconNotifyIndication =
2611  (FTDF_BeaconNotifyIndication *) FTDF_GET_MSG_BUFFER(
2612  sizeof(FTDF_BeaconNotifyIndication));
2613 
2614  beaconNotifyIndication->msgId = FTDF_BEACON_NOTIFY_INDICATION;
2615  beaconNotifyIndication->BSN = frameHeader->SN;
2616  beaconNotifyIndication->PANDescriptor = &PANDescriptor;
2617  beaconNotifyIndication->pendAddrSpec = pendAddrSpec;
2618  beaconNotifyIndication->addrList = pendAddrList;
2619  beaconNotifyIndication->sduLength = beaconPayloadLength;
2620  beaconNotifyIndication->sdu = FTDF_GET_DATA_BUFFER(beaconPayloadLength);
2621  beaconNotifyIndication->EBSN = frameHeader->SN;
2622  beaconNotifyIndication->beaconType =
2623  frameHeader->frameVersion == FTDF_FRAME_VERSION_E ? FTDF_ENHANCED_BEACON : FTDF_NORMAL_BEACON;
2624  beaconNotifyIndication->IEList = payloadIEList;
2625  beaconNotifyIndication->timestamp = timestamp;
2626 
2627  memcpy(beaconNotifyIndication->sdu, rxPtr, beaconPayloadLength);
2628 
2629  FTDF_RCV_MSG((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) beaconNotifyIndication);
2630  }
2631  else if (FTDF_reqCurrent &&
2632  FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId == FTDF_SCAN_REQUEST)
2633  {
2634  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2635  FTDF_addPANdescriptor(&PANDescriptor);
2636  }
2637  else
2638  {
2639  FTDF_REL_DATA_BUFFER((FTDF_Octet *)payloadIEList);
2640  }
2641  }
2642 
2643 #if FTDF_USE_LPDP
2644 #if FTDF_FP_BIT_TEST_MODE
2645 
2646  if (FTDF_lpdpIsEnabled() && !FTDF_reqCurrent && frameType == FTDF_DATA_FRAME)
2647  {
2648  FTDF_processTxPending(frameHeader, securityHeader);
2649  }
2650 
2651 #else /* FTDF_FP_BIT_TEST_MODE */
2652 
2653  if (!FTDF_reqCurrent && frameType == FTDF_DATA_FRAME)
2654  {
2655  FTDF_processTxPending(frameHeader, securityHeader);
2656  }
2657 
2658 #endif /* FTDF_FP_BIT_TEST_MODE */
2659 #endif /* FTDF_USE_LPDP */
2660 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
2661 
2662  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
2663  {
2664  FTDF_scheduleTsch(NULL);
2665  }
2666 
2667 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2668 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
2669 }
2670 
2671 
2672 
2673 void FTDF_processRxEvent(void)
2674 {
2675  volatile uint32_t *rxEvent = (volatile uint32_t *) IND_R_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_EVENT;
2676 
2677  if (*rxEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXSOF_E)
2678  {
2679 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2680  *rxEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXSOF_E;
2681 #else
2682  *rxEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXSOF_E;
2683 #endif
2684  }
2685 
2686  if (*rxEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXBYTE_E)
2687  {
2688 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2689  *rxEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXBYTE_E;
2690 #else
2691  *rxEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXBYTE_E;
2692 #endif
2693  }
2694 
2695  if (*rxEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_OVERFLOW_E)
2696  {
2697  // No API defined to report this error to the higher layer, so just clear it.
2698 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2699  *rxEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_OVERFLOW_E;
2700 #else
2701  *rxEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_OVERFLOW_E;
2702 #endif
2703  }
2704 
2705  if (*rxEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_BUF_AVAIL_E)
2706  {
2707  int readBuf = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_READ_BUF_PTR);
2708  int writeBuf = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_WRITE_BUF_PTR);
2709 
2710  while (readBuf != writeBuf)
2711  {
2712  processRxFrame(readBuf % 8);
2713  readBuf = (readBuf + 1) % 16;
2714  }
2715 
2716  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_READ_BUF_PTR, readBuf);
2717 
2718 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2719  *rxEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_BUF_AVAIL_E;
2720 #else
2721  *rxEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RX_BUF_AVAIL_E;
2722 #endif
2723  }
2724 
2725  volatile uint32_t *lmacEvent = (volatile uint32_t *) IND_R_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMAC_EVENT;
2726 
2727  if (*lmacEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_EDSCANREADY_E)
2728  {
2729 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2730  *lmacEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_EDSCANREADY_E;
2731 #else
2732  *lmacEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_EDSCANREADY_E;
2733 #endif
2734 
2735 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
2736  FTDF_MsgBuffer *request = FTDF_reqCurrent;
2737 
2738  if (request->msgId == FTDF_SCAN_REQUEST)
2739  {
2740  FTDF_scanReady((FTDF_ScanRequest *) request);
2741  }
2742 
2743 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
2744  }
2745 
2746  if (*lmacEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXTIMEREXPIRED_E)
2747  {
2748 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2749  *lmacEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXTIMEREXPIRED_E;
2750 #else
2751  *lmacEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_RXTIMEREXPIRED_E;
2752 #endif
2753 
2754  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
2755  {
2756  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.RxExpiredCount++;
2757  }
2758 
2759 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
2760 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
2761 
2762  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
2763  {
2764  FTDF_scheduleTsch(NULL);
2765  }
2766  else
2767 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
2768  if (FTDF_reqCurrent)
2769  {
2770  FTDF_MsgId msgId = FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId;
2771 
2772  if (msgId == FTDF_POLL_REQUEST)
2773  {
2774  FTDF_sendPollConfirm((FTDF_PollRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, FTDF_NO_DATA);
2775  }
2776  else if (msgId == FTDF_SCAN_REQUEST)
2777  {
2778  FTDF_scanReady((FTDF_ScanRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent);
2779  }
2780  else if (msgId == FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST)
2781  {
2782  FTDF_sendAssociateConfirm((FTDF_AssociateRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent,
2783  FTDF_NO_DATA,
2784  0xffff);
2785  }
2786  }
2787 
2788 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
2789  }
2790 
2791 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
2792 
2793  if (*lmacEvent & MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_THR_E)
2794  {
2795 #ifdef SIMULATOR
2796  *lmacEvent &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_THR_E;
2797 #else
2798  *lmacEvent = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_THR_E;
2799 #endif
2800 #if FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF
2801 
2802  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
2803  {
2804  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.BOIrqCount++;
2805  }
2806 
2807  FTDF_sdbFsmBackoffIRQ();
2808 #endif /* FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF */
2809  }
2810 
2811 #endif
2812 }
2813 
2814 static void sendConfirm(FTDF_Status status,
2815  FTDF_MsgId msgId)
2816 {
2817  switch (msgId)
2818  {
2819 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
2820 
2821  case FTDF_DATA_REQUEST:
2822  {
2823  FTDF_DataRequest *dataRequest = (FTDF_DataRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2824 
2825  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TXTIMESTAMP,
2826  FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2827  FTDF_SN SN = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_MACSN, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2828  FTDF_NumOfBackoffs numOfBackoffs = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_CSMACANRRETRIES,
2829  FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
2830 
2831  FTDF_sendDataConfirm(dataRequest, status,
2832  timestamp,
2833  SN,
2834  numOfBackoffs,
2835  NULL);
2836 
2837  break;
2838  }
2839 
2840  case FTDF_POLL_REQUEST:
2841 
2842  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2843  {
2844  FTDF_sendPollConfirm((FTDF_PollRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, status);
2845  }
2846 
2847  break;
2848 
2849  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
2850 
2851  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2852  {
2853  FTDF_sendAssociateConfirm((FTDF_AssociateRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent,
2854  status,
2855  0xffff);
2856  }
2857 
2858  break;
2859 
2860  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_RESPONSE:
2861 
2862  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2863  {
2864  FTDF_AssociateResponse *assocResp = (FTDF_AssociateResponse *)FTDF_reqCurrent;
2865 
2866  FTDF_Address srcAddr, dstAddr;
2867  srcAddr.extAddress = FTDF_pib.extAddress;
2868  dstAddr.extAddress = assocResp->deviceAddress;
2869 
2870  FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(FTDF_reqCurrent, status,
2871  FTDF_pib.PANId,
2872  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2873  srcAddr,
2874  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2875  dstAddr,
2876  assocResp->securityLevel,
2877  assocResp->keyIdMode,
2878  assocResp->keySource,
2879  assocResp->keyIndex);
2880  }
2881 
2882  break;
2883 
2884  case FTDF_ORPHAN_RESPONSE:
2885 
2886  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2887  {
2888  FTDF_OrphanResponse *orphanResp = (FTDF_OrphanResponse *)FTDF_reqCurrent;
2889 
2890  FTDF_Address srcAddr, dstAddr;
2891  srcAddr.extAddress = FTDF_pib.extAddress;
2892  dstAddr.extAddress = orphanResp->orphanAddress;
2893 
2894  FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(FTDF_reqCurrent, status,
2895  FTDF_pib.PANId,
2896  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2897  srcAddr,
2898  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
2899  dstAddr,
2900  orphanResp->securityLevel,
2901  orphanResp->keyIdMode,
2902  orphanResp->keySource,
2903  orphanResp->keyIndex);
2904  }
2905 
2906  break;
2907 
2908  case FTDF_DISASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
2909 
2910  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2911  {
2912  FTDF_sendDisassociateConfirm((FTDF_DisassociateRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, status);
2913  }
2914 
2915  break;
2916 
2917  case FTDF_SCAN_REQUEST:
2918 
2919  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
2920  {
2921  FTDF_sendScanConfirm((FTDF_ScanRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, status);
2922  }
2923 
2924  break;
2925 
2926  case FTDF_BEACON_REQUEST:
2927  FTDF_sendBeaconConfirm((FTDF_BeaconRequest *)FTDF_reqCurrent, status);
2928  break;
2929 
2930  case FTDF_REMOTE_REQUEST:
2931  FTDF_reqCurrent = NULL;
2932  break;
2933 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
2934 
2935  case FTDF_TRANSPARENT_REQUEST:
2936  {
2937 #ifndef FTDF_PHY_API
2938  FTDF_TransparentRequest *transparentRequest = (FTDF_TransparentRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
2939 #endif
2940  FTDF_Bitmap32 transparentStatus = 0;
2941 
2942  switch (status)
2943  {
2944  case FTDF_SUCCESS:
2945  transparentStatus = FTDF_TRANSPARENT_SEND_SUCCESSFUL;
2946  break;
2947 
2948  case FTDF_CHANNEL_ACCESS_FAILURE:
2949  transparentStatus = FTDF_TRANSPARENT_CSMACA_FAILURE;
2950  break;
2951 #if FTDF_TRANSPARENT_WAIT_FOR_ACK
2952 
2953  case FTDF_NO_ACK:
2954  transparentStatus = FTDF_TRANSPARENT_NO_ACK;
2955  break;
2956 #endif
2957  }
2958 
2959  if (FTDF_pib.metricsEnabled)
2960  {
2961  FTDF_pib.performanceMetrics.TXSuccessCount++;
2962  }
2963 
2964 #ifdef FTDF_PHY_API
2965  FTDF_criticalVar();
2966  FTDF_enterCritical();
2967  FTDF_txInProgress = FTDF_FALSE;
2968  FTDF_exitCritical();
2969 
2970  FTDF_SEND_FRAME_TRANSPARENT_CONFIRM(NULL, transparentStatus);
2971 #else
2972 
2973  FTDF_reqCurrent = NULL;
2974 
2975  FTDF_SEND_FRAME_TRANSPARENT_CONFIRM(transparentRequest->handle,
2976  transparentStatus);
2977 
2978  FTDF_REL_MSG_BUFFER((FTDF_MsgBuffer *) transparentRequest);
2979 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
2980  FTDF_processNextRequest();
2981 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
2982 
2983 #endif /* FTDF_PHY_API */
2984  break;
2985  }
2986  }

3101 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
3102 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */

3118  // rather then send again

3122  else
3123 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */

3171  }

3360 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
3361 FTDF_Status FTDF_sendFrame(FTDF_ChannelNumber channel,
3362  FTDF_FrameHeader *frameHeader,
3363  FTDF_SecurityHeader *securityHeader,
3364  FTDF_Octet *txPtr,
3365  FTDF_DataLength payloadSize,
3366  FTDF_Octet *payload)
3367 {
3368  FTDF_Octet *txBufPtr = (FTDF_Octet *) FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_FIFO);
3369 
3370  FTDF_DataLength micLength = FTDF_getMicLength(securityHeader->securityLevel);
3371  FTDF_DataLength phyPayloadSize = (txPtr - txBufPtr) - 1 + payloadSize + micLength + FTDF_FCS_LENGTH;
3372 
3373  if (phyPayloadSize > (FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH - 1))
3374  {
3375  return FTDF_FRAME_TOO_LONG;
3376  }
3377 
3378  *txBufPtr = phyPayloadSize;
3379 
3380  FTDF_Octet *privPtr = txPtr;
3381 
3382  int n;
3383 
3384  for (n = 0; n < payloadSize; n++)
3385  {
3386  *txPtr++ = *payload++;
3387  }
3388 
3389  FTDF_Status status = FTDF_secureFrame(txBufPtr,
3390  privPtr,
3391  frameHeader,
3392  securityHeader);
3393 
3394  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
3395  {
3396  return status;
3397  }
3398 
3399  FTDF_Bitmap8 options = frameHeader->options;
3400 
3401  volatile uint32_t *metaData0 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3402  volatile uint32_t *metaData1 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3403 
3404  uint16_t phyAttr = (FTDF_pib.CCAMode & 0x3) | 0x08 | ((channel - 11) & 0x0F) << 4 |
3405  (FTDF_pib.TXPower & 0x07) << 12;
3406 
3407  metaData0 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3408  metaData1 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3409 
3410  *metaData0 =
3411  ((phyPayloadSize << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) |
3412  ((phyAttr << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) |
3413  ((frameHeader->frameType << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) |
3414  MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CSMACA_ENA |
3415  ((options & FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED) ? MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_ACKREQUEST : 0) |
3416  MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CRC16_ENA;
3417 
3418  *metaData1 =
3419  ((frameHeader->SN << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN);
3420 
3421  uint32_t phyCsmaCaAttr = (FTDF_pib.CCAMode & 0x3) | ((channel - 11) & 0xf) << 4 |
3422  (FTDF_pib.TXPower & 0x07) << 12;
3423  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYCSMACAATTR, phyCsmaCaAttr);
3424 
3425 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
3426 
3427  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
3428  {
3429  if (frameHeader->dstAddrMode != FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
3430  {
3431  return FTDF_NO_SHORT_ADDRESS;
3432  }
3433 
3434  // Clear CSMACA of data frame buffer
3435  *metaData0 &= ~MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CSMACA_ENA;
3436 
3437  txPtr = txBufPtr = ((FTDF_Octet *) FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_FIFO)) +
3438  (FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH * FTDF_TX_WAKEUP_BUFFER);
3439 
3440  *txPtr++ = 0x0d;
3441  *txPtr++ = 0x2d;
3442  *txPtr++ = 0x81;
3443  *txPtr++ = frameHeader->SN;
3444  *(FTDF_PANId *) txPtr = frameHeader->dstPANId;
3445  txPtr += 2;
3446  *(FTDF_ShortAddress *) txPtr = frameHeader->dstAddr.shortAddress;
3447  txPtr += 2;
3448  *txPtr++ = 0x82;
3449  *txPtr++ = 0x0e;
3450 
3451  metaData0 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0, FTDF_TX_WAKEUP_BUFFER);
3452  metaData1 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1, FTDF_TX_WAKEUP_BUFFER);
3453  volatile uint32_t *txPriority =
3454  FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_PRIORITY, FTDF_TX_WAKEUP_BUFFER);
3455 
3456  *metaData0 =
3457  ((0x0d << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) |
3458  ((phyAttr << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) |
3459  ((FTDF_MULTIPURPOSE_FRAME << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) |
3460  MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CSMACA_ENA |
3461  MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CRC16_ENA;
3462 
3463  *metaData1 =
3464  ((frameHeader->SN << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN);
3465 #if FTDF_USE_PTI && FTDF_USE_AUTO_PTI
3466  *txPriority |= MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_ISWAKEUP;
3467 #else
3468  *txPriority = MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_ISWAKEUP;
3469 #endif
3470  }
3471 
3472 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
3473 
3474  volatile uint32_t *txFlagSet = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_SET);
3475 
3476 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
3477 
3478  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
3479  {
3480  FTDF_Time curTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
3481  FTDF_Time delta = curTime - FTDF_rzTime;
3482 
3483  if (delta > 0x80000000)
3484  {
3485  // Receiving an wakeup frame sequence, delay sending until RZ has passed.
3486  FTDF_sendFramePending = frameHeader->dstAddr.shortAddress;
3487  }
3488  else
3489  {
3490  FTDF_Time wakeupStartTime;
3491  FTDF_Period wakeupPeriod;
3492 
3493  FTDF_criticalVar();
3494  FTDF_enterCritical();
3495 
3496  FTDF_getWakeupParams(frameHeader->dstAddr.shortAddress, &wakeupStartTime, &wakeupPeriod);
3497 
3498  FTDF_txInProgress = FTDF_TRUE;
3499  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACCSLSTARTSAMPLETIME, wakeupStartTime);
3500  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACWUPERIOD, wakeupPeriod);
3501 
3502  *txFlagSet |= ((1 << FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER) | (1 << FTDF_TX_WAKEUP_BUFFER));
3503 
3504  FTDF_exitCritical();
3505  }
3506  }
3507  else
3508 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
3509  if (!FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
3510  {
3511  *txFlagSet |= (1 << FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3512 // SetWord16(P2_SET_DATA_REG, (1 << 3));
3513 // SetWord16(P23_MODE_REG, 0x300); // SW trigger - output
3514 // for (volatile int k = 0; k < 100; k++) {
3515 // }
3516 // SetWord16(P23_MODE_REG, 0x000);// SW trigger - high Z
3517 
3518 
3519  }
3520 
3521  return FTDF_SUCCESS;
3522 }
