3524 #if !defined(FTDF_NO_CSL) || !defined(FTDF_NO_TSCH)
3525 FTDF_Status FTDF_sendAckFrame(FTDF_FrameHeader *frameHeader,
3526  FTDF_SecurityHeader *securityHeader,
3527  FTDF_Octet *txPtr)
3528 {
3529  FTDF_Octet *txBufPtr = ((FTDF_Octet *) FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_FIFO)) +
3530  2 * FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH;
3531  FTDF_DataLength micLength = FTDF_getMicLength(securityHeader->securityLevel);
3532  FTDF_DataLength phyPayloadSize = (txPtr - txBufPtr) - 1 + micLength + FTDF_FCS_LENGTH;
3533 
3534  *txBufPtr = phyPayloadSize;
3535 
3536  FTDF_Status status = FTDF_secureFrame(txBufPtr,
3537  txPtr,
3538  frameHeader,
3539  securityHeader);
3540 
3541  if (status != FTDF_SUCCESS)
3542  {
3543  return status;
3544  }
3545 
3546  volatile uint32_t *metaData0 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0, FTDF_TX_ACK_BUFFER);
3547  volatile uint32_t *metaData1 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1, FTDF_TX_ACK_BUFFER);
3548  volatile uint32_t *txPriority = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_PRIORITY, FTDF_TX_ACK_BUFFER);
3549 
3550  uint16_t phyAttr =
3551  (FTDF_pib.CCAMode & 0x3) | 0x08 | (FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYRXATTR) & 0x00f0) |
3552  (FTDF_pib.TXPower & 0x07) << 12;
3553 
3554  *metaData0 =
3555  ((phyPayloadSize << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) |
3556  ((phyAttr << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) |
3557  ((FTDF_ACKNOWLEDGEMENT_FRAME << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) |
3558  MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CRC16_ENA;
3559 
3560  *metaData1 =
3561  ((frameHeader->SN << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN);
3562 
3563 #if FTDF_USE_PTI && FTDF_USE_AUTO_PTI
3564  *txPriority |= 1;
3565 #else
3566  *txPriority = 1;
3567 #endif
3568 
3569  volatile uint32_t *txFlagSet = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_SET);
3570 
3571 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
3572 
3573  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
3574  {
3575  FTDF_criticalVar();
3576  FTDF_enterCritical();
3577 
3578  FTDF_Period txAckDelayVal = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACTSTXACKDELAYVAL);
3579 
3580  if (txAckDelayVal > 20)
3581  {
3582  *txFlagSet |= 1 << FTDF_TX_ACK_BUFFER;
3583  }
3584 
3585  FTDF_exitCritical();
3586  }
3587  else
3588 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
3589  {
3590  *txFlagSet |= 1 << FTDF_TX_ACK_BUFFER;
3591  }
3592 
3593  FTDF_pib.trafficCounters.txEnhAckFrmCnt++;
3594 
3595  return FTDF_SUCCESS;
3596 }
3597 #endif /* !FTDF_NO_CSL || !FTDF_NO_TSCH */
3598 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
3599 
3600 void FTDF_sendTransparentFrame(FTDF_DataLength frameLength,
3601  FTDF_Octet *frame,
3602  FTDF_ChannelNumber channel,
3603  FTDF_PTI pti,
3604  FTDF_Boolean cmsaSuppress)
3605 {
3606  volatile uint32_t *metaData0 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3607  volatile uint32_t *metaData1 = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3608  volatile uint32_t *txPriority = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_PRIORITY, FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3609 
3610 #if FTDF_TRANSPARENT_USE_WAIT_FOR_ACK
3611  FTDF_Boolean useAck = FTDF_FALSE;
3612  //FTDF_FrameHeader* frameHeader = &FTDF_fh;
3613  FTDF_FrameHeader frameHeader;
3614  FTDF_SN SN;
3615 #endif
3616  uint16_t phyAttr = (FTDF_pib.CCAMode & 0x3) | 0x08 | ((channel - 11) & 0x0F) << 4 |
3617  (FTDF_pib.TXPower & 0x07) << 12;
3618 #if FTDF_TRANSPARENT_USE_WAIT_FOR_ACK
3619 
3620  if (FTDF_transparentModeOptions & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_WAIT_FOR_ACK)
3621  {
3622  FTDF_getFrameHeader(frame, &frameHeader);
3623 
3624  if (frameHeader.options & FTDF_OPT_ACK_REQUESTED)
3625  {
3626  useAck = FTDF_TRUE;
3627  }
3628 
3629  SN = frameHeader.SN;
3630  }
3631 
3632 #endif
3633 
3634 #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A
3635  *txPriority = ((pti << OFF_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PTI_TX) &
3636  MSK_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_PTI_TX) | 1;
3637 #endif
3638  *metaData0 =
3639  ((frameLength << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAME_LENGTH) |
3640  ((phyAttr << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_PHYATTR) |
3641  (((*frame & 0x7) << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_FRAMETYPE) |
3642  ((cmsaSuppress) ? 0 : MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CSMACA_ENA) |
3643 #if FTDF_TRANSPARENT_USE_WAIT_FOR_ACK
3644  ((useAck) ? MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_ACKREQUEST : 0) |
3645 #endif
3646  ((FTDF_transparentModeOptions &
3647  FTDF_TRANSPARENT_ENABLE_FCS_GENERATION) ? MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_CRC16_ENA : 0);
3648 
3649 #if FTDF_TRANSPARENT_USE_WAIT_FOR_ACK
3650 
3651  if (useAck)
3652  {
3653  *metaData1 = ((SN << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN);
3654  }
3655  else
3656  {
3657  *metaData1 = ((0 << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN);
3658  }
3659 
3660 #else
3661  *metaData1 =
3662  ((0 << OFF_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN) & MSK_F_FTDF_RETENTION_RAM_MACSN);
3663 #endif
3664 
3665  uint32_t phyCsmaCaAttr = (FTDF_pib.CCAMode & 0x3) | ((channel - 11) & 0xf) << 4 |
3666  (FTDF_pib.TXPower & 0x07) << 12;
3667  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYCSMACAATTR, phyCsmaCaAttr);
3668 #if FTDF_USE_PTI && !FTDF_USE_AUTO_PTI
3669  hw_coex_update_ftdf_pti((hw_coex_pti_t) pti, NULL, true);
3670 #else
3671  // FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PTI_TX, pti);
3672 #endif
3673  volatile uint32_t *txFlagSet = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_SET);
3674  *txFlagSet |= (1 << FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
3675 }

3677 void FTDF_initQueues(void)
3678 {

3681  FTDF_initQueue(&FTDF_reqQueue);

3686  {

3688 
3689  FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addr.extAddress = 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFLL;
3690  FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addrMode = FTDF_NO_ADDRESS;
3691  FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].PANId = 0xFFFF;

3693

3695  FTDF_txPendingTimerList[ n ].next = NULL;
3696  }
3697 
3698  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead = FTDF_txPendingTimerList;
3699  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = 0;
3700 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
3701 #ifndef FTDF_PHY_API
3702  FTDF_reqCurrent = NULL;
3703 #endif
3704 }

3706 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
3707 void FTDF_initQueue(FTDF_Queue *queue)
3708 {
3709  queue->head.next = (FTDF_Buffer *) &queue->tail;
3710  queue->head.prev = NULL;
3711  queue->tail.next = NULL;
3712  queue->tail.prev = (FTDF_Buffer *) &queue->head;
3713 }
3714 
3715 void FTDF_queueBufferHead(FTDF_Buffer *buffer, FTDF_Queue *queue)
3716 {
3717  FTDF_Buffer *next = queue->head.next;
3718 
3719  queue->head.next = buffer;
3720  next->header.prev = buffer;
3721  buffer->header.next = next;
3722  buffer->header.prev = (FTDF_Buffer *) &queue->head;
3723 }
3724 
3725 FTDF_Buffer *FTDF_dequeueBufferTail(FTDF_Queue *queue)
3726 {
3727  FTDF_Buffer *buffer = queue->tail.prev;
3728 
3729  if (buffer->header.prev == NULL)
3730  {
3731  return NULL;
3732  }
3733 
3734  queue->tail.prev = buffer->header.prev;
3735  buffer->header.prev->header.next = (FTDF_Buffer *) &queue->tail;
3736 
3737  return buffer;
3738 }
3739 
3740 FTDF_Status FTDF_queueReqHead(FTDF_MsgBuffer *request, FTDF_Queue *queue)
3741 {
3742  FTDF_Buffer *buffer = FTDF_dequeueBufferTail(&FTDF_freeQueue);
3743 
3744  if (buffer == NULL)
3745  {
3746  return FTDF_TRANSACTION_OVERFLOW;
3747  }
3748 
3749  FTDF_Buffer *next = queue->head.next;
3750 
3751  queue->head.next = buffer;
3752  next->header.prev = buffer;
3753  buffer->header.next = next;
3754  buffer->header.prev = (FTDF_Buffer *) &queue->head;
3755  buffer->request = request;
3756 
3757  return FTDF_SUCCESS;
3758 }
3759 
3760 FTDF_MsgBuffer *FTDF_dequeueReqTail(FTDF_Queue *queue)
3761 {
3762  FTDF_Buffer *buffer = queue->tail.prev;
3763 
3764  if (buffer->header.prev == NULL)
3765  {
3766  return NULL;
3767  }
3768 
3769  queue->tail.prev = buffer->header.prev;
3770  buffer->header.prev->header.next = (FTDF_Buffer *) &queue->tail;
3771 
3772  FTDF_MsgBuffer *request = buffer->request;
3773 
3774  FTDF_queueBufferHead(buffer, &FTDF_freeQueue);
3775 
3776  return request;
3777 }

3779 FTDF_MsgBuffer *FTDF_dequeueByHandle(FTDF_Handle handle, FTDF_Queue *queue)
3780 {
3781  FTDF_Buffer *buffer = queue->head.next;
3782 
3783  while (buffer->header.next != NULL)
3784  {
3785  if (buffer->request &&
3786  buffer->request->msgId == FTDF_DATA_REQUEST &&
3787  ((FTDF_DataRequest *) buffer->request)->msduHandle == handle)
3788  {
3789  buffer->header.prev->header.next = buffer->header.next;
3790  buffer->header.next->header.prev = buffer->header.prev;
3791 
3792  FTDF_MsgBuffer *request = buffer->request;
3793 
3794  FTDF_queueBufferHead(buffer, &FTDF_freeQueue);
3795 
3796  return request;
3797  }
3798 
3799  buffer = buffer->header.next;
3800  }
3801 
3802  return NULL;
3803 }
3804 
3805 FTDF_MsgBuffer *FTDF_dequeueByRequest(FTDF_MsgBuffer *request, FTDF_Queue *queue)
3806 {
3807  FTDF_Buffer *buffer = queue->head.next;
3808 
3809  while (buffer->header.next != NULL)
3810  {
3811  if (buffer->request == request)
3812  {
3813  buffer->header.prev->header.next = buffer->header.next;
3814  buffer->header.next->header.prev = buffer->header.prev;
3815 
3816  FTDF_MsgBuffer *req = buffer->request;
3817 
3818  FTDF_queueBufferHead(buffer, &FTDF_freeQueue);
3819 
3820  return req;
3821  }
3822 
3823  buffer = buffer->header.next;
3824  }
3825 
3826  return NULL;
3827 }

3829 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_isQueueEmpty(FTDF_Queue *queue)
3830 {
3831  if (queue->head.next->header.next == NULL)
3832  {
3833  return FTDF_TRUE;
3834  }
3835  else
3836  {
3837  return FTDF_FALSE;
3838  }
3839 }

3841 static FTDF_PendingTL *FTDF_findFreePendingTimer(void)
3842 {
3843  uint8_t i;
3844 
3845  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_NR_OF_REQ_BUFFERS; i++)
3846  {
3847  if (FTDF_txPendingTimerList[ i ].free == FTDF_TRUE)
3848  {
3849  break;
3850  }
3851  }
3852 
3853  return &FTDF_txPendingTimerList[ i ];
3854 }

3856 void FTDF_addTxPendingTimer(FTDF_MsgBuffer *request, uint8_t pendListNr, FTDF_Time delta, void (* func)(
3857  FTDF_PendingTL *))
3858 {
3859  FTDF_criticalVar();
3860  FTDF_enterCritical();
3861 
3862  FTDF_PendingTL *ptr = FTDF_txPendingTimerHead;
3863  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
3864 
3865  if (ptr->free == FTDF_FALSE)
3866  {
3867  while (ptr)
3868  {
3869  ptr->delta -= timestamp - FTDF_txPendingTimerLT;
3870  ptr = ptr->next;
3871  }
3872  }
3873 
3874  FTDF_txPendingTimerLT = timestamp;
3875  ptr = FTDF_txPendingTimerHead;
3876 
3877  if (ptr->free == FTDF_TRUE)
3878  {
3879  ptr->free = FTDF_FALSE;
3880  ptr->next = NULL;
3881  ptr->request = request;
3882  ptr->delta = delta;
3883  ptr->pendListNr = pendListNr;
3884  ptr->func = func;
3885 
3886  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR, delta + timestamp);
3887  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = delta + timestamp;
3888  FTDF_exitCritical();
3889  return;
3890  }
3891 
3892  if (ptr->delta > delta)
3893  {
3894  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead = FTDF_findFreePendingTimer();
3895  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead->free = FTDF_FALSE;
3896  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead->next = ptr;
3897  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead->request = request;
3898  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead->delta = delta;
3899  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead->pendListNr = pendListNr;
3900  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead->func = func;
3901 
3902  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR, delta + timestamp);
3903  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = delta + timestamp;
3904  FTDF_exitCritical();
3905  return;
3906  }
3907  else if (ptr->delta == delta)
3908  {
3909  delta++;
3910  }
3911 
3912  FTDF_PendingTL *prev;
3913 
3914  while (ptr->next)
3915  {
3916  prev = ptr;
3917  ptr = ptr->next;
3918 
3919  if (ptr->delta == delta)
3920  {
3921  delta++;
3922  }
3923 
3924  if (prev->delta < delta && ptr->delta > delta)
3925  {
3926  prev->next = FTDF_findFreePendingTimer();
3927  prev->next->next = ptr;
3928  ptr = prev->next;
3929  ptr->free = FTDF_FALSE;
3930  ptr->request = request;
3931  ptr->delta = delta;
3932  ptr->pendListNr = pendListNr;
3933  ptr->func = func;
3934 
3935  FTDF_exitCritical();
3936  return;
3937  }
3938  }
3939 
3940  ptr->next = FTDF_findFreePendingTimer();
3941  ptr = ptr->next;
3942  ptr->free = FTDF_FALSE;
3943  ptr->next = NULL;
3944  ptr->request = request;
3945  ptr->delta = delta;
3946  ptr->pendListNr = pendListNr;
3947  ptr->func = func;
3948 
3949  FTDF_exitCritical();
3950 }
3951 
3952 void FTDF_removeTxPendingTimer(FTDF_MsgBuffer *request)
3953 {
3954  FTDF_criticalVar();
3955  FTDF_enterCritical();
3956 
3957  FTDF_PendingTL *ptr = FTDF_txPendingTimerHead;
3958  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
3959 
3960  if (ptr->free == FTDF_TRUE)
3961  {
3962  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR, timestamp - 1);
3963  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = timestamp - 1;
3964  FTDF_exitCritical();
3965  return;
3966  }
3967 
3968  while (ptr)
3969  {
3970  ptr->delta -= timestamp - FTDF_txPendingTimerLT;
3971  ptr = ptr->next;
3972  }
3973 
3974  FTDF_txPendingTimerLT = timestamp;
3975  ptr = FTDF_txPendingTimerHead;
3976 
3977  if (!request || ptr->request == request)
3978  {
3979  if (ptr->next)
3980  {
3981  FTDF_PendingTL *temp = ptr;
3982 
3983  if (ptr->next->delta < 75)
3984  {
3985  while (temp)
3986  {
3987  temp->delta += 75;
3988  temp = temp->next;
3989  }
3990  }
3991 
3992  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR, timestamp + ptr->next->delta);
3993  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = timestamp + ptr->next->delta;
3994  FTDF_txPendingTimerHead = ptr->next;
3995 
3996  ptr->free = FTDF_TRUE;
3997  ptr->next = NULL;
3998  }
3999  else
4000  {
4001  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR, timestamp - 1);
4002  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = timestamp - 1;
4003 
4004  ptr->free = FTDF_TRUE;
4005  ptr->next = NULL;
4006  }
4007 
4008  FTDF_exitCritical();
4009 
4010  if (!request)
4011  {
4012  if (ptr->func)
4013  {
4014  ptr->func(ptr);
4015  }
4016  }
4017 
4018  return;
4019  }
4020 
4021  FTDF_PendingTL *prev = ptr;
4022 
4023  while (ptr->next)
4024  {
4025  prev = ptr;
4026  ptr = ptr->next;
4027 
4028  if (ptr->request == request)
4029  {
4030  prev->next = ptr->next;
4031  ptr->free = FTDF_TRUE;
4032  ptr->next = NULL;
4033 
4034  FTDF_exitCritical();
4035  return;
4036  }
4037  }
4038 
4039  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMETHR, timestamp - 1);
4040  FTDF_txPendingTimerTime = timestamp - 1;
4041  FTDF_exitCritical();
4042 }

4047 }

4059  return FTDF_TRUE;

4074 
4075 void FTDF_sendTransactionExpired(FTDF_PendingTL *ptr)
4076 {
4077  FTDF_MsgBuffer *req =
4078  FTDF_dequeueByRequest(ptr->request, &FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].queue);
4079 
4080  if (!req)
4081  {
4082  return;
4083  }
4084 
4085  if (FTDF_isQueueEmpty(&FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].queue))
4086  {
4087 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
4088 
4089  if (FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
4090  {
4091  FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].addr.shortAddress = 0xfffe;
4092  }
4093  else
4094 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
4095  {
4096 #if FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO
4097 
4098  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].addrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
4099  {
4100  uint8_t entry, shortAddrIdx;
4101  FTDF_Boolean found = FTDF_fpprLookupShortAddress(
4102  FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].addr.shortAddress, &entry,
4103  &shortAddrIdx);
4104  ASSERT_WARNING(found);
4105  FTDF_fpprSetShortAddressValid(entry, shortAddrIdx, FTDF_FALSE);
4106  }
4107  else if (FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].addrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
4108  {
4109  uint8_t entry;
4110  FTDF_Boolean found = FTDF_fpprLookupExtAddress(
4111  FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].addr.extAddress, &entry);
4112  ASSERT_WARNING(found);
4113  FTDF_fpprSetExtAddressValid(entry, FTDF_FALSE);
4114  }
4115  else
4116  {
4117  ASSERT_WARNING(0);
4118  }
4119 
4120 #endif /* FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO */
4121  FTDF_txPendingList[ ptr->pendListNr ].addrMode = FTDF_NO_ADDRESS;
4122  }
4123  }
4124 
4125  switch (req->msgId)
4126  {
4127  case FTDF_DATA_REQUEST:
4128  {
4129  FTDF_DataRequest *dataRequest = (FTDF_DataRequest *)req;
4130 
4131  FTDF_sendDataConfirm(dataRequest, FTDF_TRANSACTION_EXPIRED, 0, 0, 0, NULL);
4132 
4133  break;
4134  }
4135 
4136  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
4137  {
4138  FTDF_AssociateRequest *associateRequest = (FTDF_AssociateRequest *)req;
4139 
4140  FTDF_sendAssociateConfirm(associateRequest, FTDF_TRANSACTION_EXPIRED, 0xffff);
4141 
4142  break;
4143  }
4144 
4145  case FTDF_ASSOCIATE_RESPONSE:
4146  {
4147  FTDF_AssociateResponse *assocResp = (FTDF_AssociateResponse *)req;
4148 
4149  FTDF_Address srcAddr, dstAddr;
4150  srcAddr.extAddress = FTDF_pib.extAddress;
4151  dstAddr.extAddress = assocResp->deviceAddress;
4152 
4153  FTDF_sendCommStatusIndication(req, FTDF_TRANSACTION_EXPIRED,
4154  FTDF_pib.PANId,
4155  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
4156  srcAddr,
4157  FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS,
4158  dstAddr,
4159  assocResp->securityLevel,
4160  assocResp->keyIdMode,
4161  assocResp->keySource,
4162  assocResp->keyIndex);
4163 
4164  break;
4165  }
4166 
4167  case FTDF_DISASSOCIATE_REQUEST:
4168  {
4169  FTDF_DisassociateRequest *disReq = (FTDF_DisassociateRequest *)req;
4170 
4171  FTDF_sendDisassociateConfirm(disReq, FTDF_TRANSACTION_EXPIRED);
4172 
4173  break;
4174  }
4175 
4176  case FTDF_BEACON_REQUEST:
4177  {
4178  FTDF_BeaconRequest *beaconRequest = (FTDF_BeaconRequest *)req;
4179 
4180  FTDF_sendBeaconConfirm(beaconRequest, FTDF_TRANSACTION_EXPIRED);
4181 
4182  break;
4183  }
4184  }
4185 }
4186 
4187 #ifndef FTDF_NO_TSCH
4188 void FTDF_resetKeepAliveTimer(FTDF_ShortAddress dstAddr)
4189 {
4190  uint8_t n;
4191 
4192  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_NEIGHBORS; n++)
4193  {
4194  if (FTDF_neighborTable[ n ].dstAddr == dstAddr)
4195  {
4196  break;
4197  }
4198  }
4199 
4200  if (n == FTDF_NR_OF_NEIGHBORS)
4201  {
4202  return;
4203  }
4204 
4205  FTDF_removeTxPendingTimer((FTDF_MsgBuffer *)&FTDF_neighborTable[ n ].msg);
4206 
4207  FTDF_Time tsTimeslotLength = (FTDF_Time) FTDF_pib.timeslotTemplate.tsTimeslotLength / 16;
4208  FTDF_Time delta = tsTimeslotLength * FTDF_neighborTable[ n ].period;
4209 
4210  FTDF_addTxPendingTimer((FTDF_MsgBuffer *)&FTDF_neighborTable[ n ].msg, n, delta, FTDF_processKeepAliveTimerExp);
4211 }
4212 #endif /* FTDF_NO_TSCH */
4213 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */

4215 void FTDF_enableTransparentMode(FTDF_Boolean enable,
4216  FTDF_Bitmap32 options)
4217 {
4218 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
4219 
4220  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled == FTDF_TRUE ||
4221  FTDF_pib.tschEnabled == FTDF_TRUE)
4222  {
4223  return;
4224  }
4225 
4226 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
4227 
4228  FTDF_transparentMode = enable;
4229  FTDF_transparentModeOptions = options;
4230 
4231  if (enable)
4232  {
4233  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSFRMTYPE,
4234  (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_ALL_FRAME_TYPES));
4235  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_DISRXACKREQUESTCA, (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_AUTO_ACK ? 0 : 1));
4236  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSCRCERROR, (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_CRC_ERROR ? 1 : 0));
4237  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSRESFRAMEVERSION,
4238  (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_ALL_FRAME_VERSION ? 1 : 0));
4239  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSWRONGDPANID,
4240  (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_ALL_PAN_ID ? 1 : 0));
4241  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSWRONGDADDR, (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_ALL_ADDR ? 1 : 0));
4242  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSBEACONWRONGPANID,
4243  (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_ALL_BEACON ? 1 : 0));
4244  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSTOPANCOORDINATOR,
4245  (options & FTDF_TRANSPARENT_PASS_ALL_NO_DEST_ADDR ? 1 : 0));
4246  }
4247  else
4248  {
4249  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSFRMTYPE, 0);
4250  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_DISRXACKREQUESTCA, 0);
4251  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSCRCERROR, 0);
4252  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSRESFRAMEVERSION, 0);
4253  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSWRONGDPANID, 0);
4254  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSWRONGDADDR, 0);
4255  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSBEACONWRONGPANID, 0);
4256  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACALWAYSPASSTOPANCOORDINATOR, 0);
4257  }
4258 }

4278 #ifndef FTDF_LITE
4279 #ifndef FTDF_NO_CSL
4280 void FTDF_setPeerCslTiming(FTDF_IEList *headerIEList, FTDF_Time timeStamp)
4281 {
4282  if (FTDF_reqCurrent->msgId != FTDF_DATA_REQUEST)
4283  {
4284  // Only use the CSL timing of data frame acks
4285  return;
4286  }
4287 
4288  FTDF_DataRequest *dataRequest = (FTDF_DataRequest *) FTDF_reqCurrent;
4289  FTDF_ShortAddress dstAddr = dataRequest->dstAddr.shortAddress;
4290 
4291  if (dataRequest->dstAddrMode != FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS ||
4292  dstAddr == 0xffff)
4293  {
4294  return;
4295  }
4296 
4297  int n;
4298 
4299  // Search for an existing entry
4300  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS; n++)
4301  {
4302  if (FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].addr == dstAddr)
4303  {
4304  break;
4305  }
4306  }
4307 
4308  if (headerIEList == NULL)
4309  {
4310  if (n < FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS)
4311  {
4312  // Delete entry
4313  FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].addr = 0xffff;
4314  }
4315 
4316  return;
4317  }
4318 
4319  int ieNr = 0;
4320 
4321  while (ieNr < headerIEList->nrOfIEs &&
4322  headerIEList->IEs[ ieNr ].ID != 0x1a)
4323  {
4324  ieNr++;
4325  }
4326 
4327  if (ieNr == headerIEList->nrOfIEs)
4328  {
4329  return;
4330  }
4331 
4332  if (n == FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS)
4333  {
4334  // Search for an empty entry
4335  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS; n++)
4336  {
4337  if (FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].addr == 0xffff)
4338  {
4339  break;
4340  }
4341  }
4342  }
4343 
4344  if (n == FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS)
4345  {
4346  // No free entry, search for the least recently used entry
4347  FTDF_Time maxDelta = 0;
4348  int lru = 0;
4349 
4350  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS; n++)
4351  {
4352  FTDF_Time delta = timeStamp - FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].time;
4353 
4354  if (delta > maxDelta)
4355  {
4356  maxDelta = delta;
4357  lru = n;
4358  }
4359  }
4360 
4361  n = lru;
4362  }
4363 
4364  FTDF_Period phase = (*(FTDF_Period *)(headerIEList->IEs[ 0 ].content.raw + 0));
4365  FTDF_Period period = (*(FTDF_Period *)(headerIEList->IEs[ 0 ].content.raw + 2));
4366 
4367  FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].addr = dstAddr;
4368  FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].time = timeStamp - (phase * 10);
4369  FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].period = period;
4370 }
4371 
4372 void FTDF_getWakeupParams(FTDF_ShortAddress dstAddr,
4373  FTDF_Time *wakeupStartTime,
4374  FTDF_Period *wakeupPeriod)
4375 {
4376  int n;
4377 
4378  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS; n++)
4379  {
4380  if (FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].addr == dstAddr)
4381  {
4382  break;
4383  }
4384  }
4385 
4386  FTDF_Time curTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
4387 
4388  if (dstAddr == 0xffff ||
4389  n == FTDF_NR_OF_CSL_PEERS)
4390  {
4391  *wakeupStartTime = curTime + 5;
4392  *wakeupPeriod = FTDF_pib.CSLMaxPeriod;
4393 
4394  return;
4395  }
4396 
4397  FTDF_Time peerTime = FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].time;
4398  FTDF_Time peerPeriod = FTDF_peerCslTiming[ n ].period * 10;
4399  FTDF_Time delta = curTime - peerTime;
4400 
4401  if (delta > (uint32_t)(FTDF_pib.CSLMaxAgeRemoteInfo * 10))
4402  {
4403  *wakeupStartTime = curTime + 5;
4404  *wakeupPeriod = FTDF_pib.CSLMaxPeriod;
4405 
4406  return;
4407  }
4408 
4409  FTDF_Time wStart = peerTime + (((delta / peerPeriod) + 1) * peerPeriod) - FTDF_pib.CSLSyncTxMargin;
4410  delta = wStart - curTime;
4411 
4412  if (delta < 3 || delta > 0x80000000) // A delta larger than 0x80000000 is assumed a negative delta
4413  {
4414  wStart += peerPeriod;
4415  }
4416 
4417  *wakeupPeriod = (FTDF_pib.CSLSyncTxMargin / 10) * 2;
4418  *wakeupStartTime = wStart;
4419 }
4420 
4421 void FTDF_setCslSampleTime(void)
4422 {
4423  FTDF_Time CSLPeriod = FTDF_pib.CSLPeriod * 10;
4424 
4425  FTDF_criticalVar();
4426  FTDF_enterCritical();
4427 
4428  FTDF_Time curTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
4429  FTDF_Time delta = (curTime - FTDF_startCslSampleTime);
4430 
4431  // A delta larger than 0x80000000 is assumed a negative delta, in this case the sample time does
4432  // not need to be updated.
4433  if (delta < 0x80000000)
4434  {
4435  if (delta < CSLPeriod)
4436  {
4437  FTDF_startCslSampleTime += CSLPeriod;
4438 
4439  if (delta < 3)
4440  {
4441  // To avoid to set the CSL sample time to a time stamp in the past set it to a sample period later
4442  // if the next sample would be within 3 symbols.
4443  FTDF_startCslSampleTime += CSLPeriod;
4444  }
4445  }
4446  else
4447  {
4448  FTDF_startCslSampleTime = FTDF_startCslSampleTime + ((delta / CSLPeriod) + 1) * CSLPeriod;
4449  }
4450 
4451  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_MACCSLSTARTSAMPLETIME, FTDF_startCslSampleTime);
4452  }
4453 
4454  FTDF_exitCritical();
4455 }
4456 #endif /* FTDF_NO_CSL */
4457 #endif /* !FTDF_LITE */
4458 
4459 FTDF_Time64 FTDF_getCurTime64(void)
4460 {
4461  FTDF_Time newTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
4462 
4463  if (newTime < FTDF_curTime[ 0 ])
4464  {
4465  FTDF_curTime[ 1 ]++;
4466  }
4467 
4468  FTDF_curTime[ 0 ] = newTime;
4469 
4470  return *(FTDF_Time64 *)FTDF_curTime;
4471 }
4472

4476  FTDF_curTime[ 1 ] = 0;
4477 }

4792 void FTDF_fpFsmClearPending(void)
4793 {
4794 #if FTDF_FPPR_DEFER_INVALIDATION
4795  int n;
4796 
4797  if (FTDF_fpprPending.addrMode == FTDF_NO_ADDRESS)
4798  {
4799  return;
4800  }
4801 
4802  if (FTDF_fpprPending.addrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
4803  {
4804  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_REQ_BUFFERS; n++)
4805  {
4806  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addrMode == FTDF_SHORT_ADDRESS)
4807  {
4808  if ((FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].PANId == FTDF_fpprPending.PANId) &&
4809  (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addr.shortAddress ==
4810  FTDF_fpprPending.addr.shortAddress))
4811  {
4812  return;
4813  }
4814  }
4815  }
4816 
4817  // Address not found.
4818  uint8_t entry;
4819  uint8_t shortAddrIdx;
4820  FTDF_Boolean found = FTDF_fpprLookupShortAddress(
4821  FTDF_fpprPending.addr.shortAddress, &entry, &shortAddrIdx);
4822  ASSERT_WARNING(found);
4823  FTDF_fpprSetShortAddressValid(entry, shortAddrIdx, FTDF_FALSE);
4824  }
4825  else if (FTDF_fpprPending.addrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
4826  {
4827  for (n = 0; n < FTDF_NR_OF_REQ_BUFFERS; n++)
4828  {
4829  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addrMode == FTDF_EXTENDED_ADDRESS)
4830  {
4831  if (FTDF_txPendingList[ n ].addr.extAddress ==
4832  FTDF_fpprPending.addr.extAddress)
4833  {
4834  return;
4835  }
4836  }
4837  }
4838 
4839  // Address not found.
4840  uint8_t entry;
4841  FTDF_Boolean found = FTDF_fpprLookupExtAddress(FTDF_fpprPending.addr.extAddress,
4842  &entry);
4843  ASSERT_WARNING(found);
4844  FTDF_fpprSetExtAddressValid(entry, FTDF_FALSE);
4845  }
4846  else
4847  {
4848 
4849  }
4850 
4851  FTDF_fpprPending.addrMode = FTDF_NO_ADDRESS;
4852 #endif /* FTDF_FPPR_DEFER_INVALIDATION */
4853 }
4854 
4855 #endif /* #ifndef FTDF_LITE */
4856 /*********************************** FPPR low-level access ****************************************/
4857 void FTDF_fpprReset(void)
4858 {
4859  unsigned int i;
4860 
4861  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES; i++)
4862  {
4863  *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SIZE_AND_VAL, i) = 0;
4864  }
4865 }
4866 
4867 FTDF_ShortAddress FTDF_fpprGetShortAddress(uint8_t entry, uint8_t shortAddrIdx)
4868 {
4869  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4870 
4871  switch (shortAddrIdx)
4872  {
4873  case 0:
4874  return (FTDF_ShortAddress)
4875  * FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry) &
4876  0x0000ffff;
4877 
4878  case 1:
4879  return (FTDF_ShortAddress)
4880  (*FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry) >> 16) &
4881  0x0000ffff;
4882 
4883  case 2:
4884  return (FTDF_ShortAddress)
4885  * FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry) &
4886  0x0000ffff;
4887 
4888  case 3:
4889  return (FTDF_ShortAddress)
4890  (*FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry) >> 16) &
4891  0x0000ffff;
4892 
4893  default:
4894  ASSERT_WARNING(0);
4895  }
4896 }
4897 
4898 void FTDF_fpprSetShortAddress(uint8_t entry, uint8_t shortAddrIdx,
4899  FTDF_ShortAddress shortAddress)
4900 {
4901  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4902  uint32_t val32;
4903 
4904  switch (shortAddrIdx)
4905  {
4906  case 0:
4907  val32 = *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry);
4908  val32 &= 0xffff0000;
4909  val32 |= (shortAddress & 0x0000ffff);
4910  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry) = val32;
4911  break;
4912 
4913  case 1:
4914  val32 = *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry);
4915  val32 &= 0x0000ffff;
4916  val32 |= (shortAddress & 0x0000ffff) << 16;
4917  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry) = val32;
4918  break;
4919 
4920  case 2:
4921  val32 = *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry);
4922  val32 &= 0xffff0000;
4923  val32 |= (shortAddress & 0x0000ffff);
4924  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry) = val32;
4925  break;
4926 
4927  case 3:
4928  val32 = *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry);
4929  val32 &= 0x0000ffff;
4930  val32 |= (shortAddress & 0x0000ffff) << 16;
4931  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry) = val32;
4932  break;
4933 
4934  default:
4935  ASSERT_WARNING(0);
4936  }
4937 }
4938 
4939 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_fpprGetShortAddressValid(uint8_t entry, uint8_t shortAddrIdx)
4940 {
4941  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4942  ASSERT_WARNING(shortAddrIdx < 4);
4943  uint32_t val32;
4944  val32 = *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA, entry);
4945  return ((val32 & (MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SHORT_LONGNOT | (1 << shortAddrIdx))) ==
4946  (MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SHORT_LONGNOT | (1 << shortAddrIdx))) ?
4947  FTDF_TRUE : FTDF_FALSE;
4948 }
4949 
4950 void FTDF_fpprSetShortAddressValid(uint8_t entry, uint8_t shortAddrIdx,
4951  FTDF_Boolean valid)
4952 {
4953  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4954  ASSERT_WARNING(shortAddrIdx < 4);
4955  uint32_t val32;
4956  val32 = *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA, entry);
4957 
4958  if (valid)
4959  {
4960  val32 |= MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SHORT_LONGNOT | (1 << shortAddrIdx); /* Also indicate short address. */
4961  }
4962  else
4963  {
4964  val32 &= ~(1 << shortAddrIdx);
4965  }
4966 
4967  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA, entry) = val32;
4968 }
4969 
4970 FTDF_ExtAddress FTDF_fpprGetExtAddress(uint8_t entry)
4971 {
4972  FTDF_ExtAddress extAddress;
4973  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4974  extAddress = (FTDF_ExtAddress) * FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H,
4975  entry) << 32;
4976  extAddress |= (FTDF_ExtAddress) * FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L,
4977  entry);
4978  return extAddress;
4979 }
4980 
4981 void FTDF_fpprSetExtAddress(uint8_t entry, FTDF_ExtAddress extAddress)
4982 {
4983  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4984  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, entry) =
4985  (uint32_t)(extAddress);
4986  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, entry) =
4987  (uint32_t)((extAddress >> 32));
4988 }
4989 
4990 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_fpprGetExtAddressValid(uint8_t entry)
4991 {
4992  return (*FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA, entry) == 0x1) ?
4993  FTDF_TRUE : FTDF_FALSE;
4994 }
4995 
4996 void FTDF_fpprSetExtAddressValid(uint8_t entry, FTDF_Boolean valid)
4997 {
4998  ASSERT_WARNING(entry < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES);
4999 
5000  if (valid)
5001  {
5002  /* Also indicate ext address. */
5003  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA, entry) = 0x1;
5004  }
5005  else
5006  {
5007  *FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA, entry) = 0x0;
5008  }
5009 }
5010 
5011 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_fpprGetFreeShortAddress(uint8_t *entry, uint8_t *shortAddrIdx)
5012 {
5013  int i, j;
5014  uint32_t sizeAndVal;
5015  int emptyEntry;
5016  bool emptyFound = false, nonEmptyFound = false;
5017 
5018  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES; i++)
5019  {
5020  sizeAndVal = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SIZE_AND_VAL, i);
5021 
5022  if (sizeAndVal == 0x1)
5023  {
5024  /* Check if there is a valid extended address. */
5025  continue;
5026  }
5027  else if ((sizeAndVal & MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SHORT_LONGNOT) == 0)
5028  {
5029  /* There is an invalid extended address, ignore SA valid bits */
5030  sizeAndVal = 0;
5031  }
5032  else
5033  {
5034  /* There is a SA. We are interested in bits V0 - V3. */
5035  sizeAndVal &= 0xf;
5036  }
5037 
5038  /* Check if entire entry is free. */
5039  if (sizeAndVal == 0)
5040  {
5041  /* We prefer to use partially full entries. Make note of this and
5042  * continue. */
5043  if (!emptyFound)
5044  {
5045  emptyEntry = i;
5046  emptyFound = true;
5047  }
5048 
5049  continue;
5050  }
5051 
5052  /* Check for free short address entries. */
5053  sizeAndVal = (~sizeAndVal) & 0xf;
5054  j = 0;
5055 
5056  while (sizeAndVal)
5057  {
5058  if (sizeAndVal & 0x1)
5059  {
5060  nonEmptyFound = true;
5061  break;
5062  }
5063 
5064  sizeAndVal >>= 1;
5065  j++;
5066  }
5067 
5068  if (nonEmptyFound)
5069  {
5070  break;
5071  }
5072  }
5073 
5074  if (nonEmptyFound)
5075  {
5076  *entry = i;
5077  *shortAddrIdx = j;
5078  }
5079  else if (emptyFound)
5080  {
5081  *entry = emptyEntry;
5082  *shortAddrIdx = 0;
5083  }
5084  else
5085  {
5086  return FTDF_FALSE;
5087  }
5088 
5089  return FTDF_TRUE;
5090 }
5091 
5092 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_fpprGetFreeExtAddress(uint8_t *entry)
5093 {
5094  int i;
5095  uint32_t sizeAndVal;
5096  bool found = false;
5097 
5098  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES; i++)
5099  {
5100  sizeAndVal = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SIZE_AND_VAL, i);
5101 
5102  /* Check if there is no valid extended or short address. */
5103  if (!sizeAndVal || (sizeAndVal == MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SHORT_LONGNOT))
5104  {
5105  found = true;
5106  break;
5107  }
5108  }
5109 
5110  if (found)
5111  {
5112  *entry = i;
5113  }
5114  else
5115  {
5116  return FTDF_FALSE;
5117  }
5118 
5119  return FTDF_TRUE;
5120 }
5121 
5122 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_fpprLookupShortAddress(FTDF_ShortAddress shortAddr, uint8_t *entry,
5123  uint8_t *shortAddrIdx)
5124 {
5125  uint8_t i;
5126  uint32_t sizeAndVal;
5127  uint32_t saPart;
5128 
5129  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES; i++)
5130  {
5131  sizeAndVal = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SIZE_AND_VAL, i);
5132 
5133  /* Check if there is a valid short address. */
5134  if (!(sizeAndVal & MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SHORT_LONGNOT) ||
5135  !(sizeAndVal & MSK_F_FTDF_FP_PROCESSING_RAM_VALID_SA))
5136  {
5137  continue;
5138  }
5139 
5140  saPart = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, i);
5141 
5142  if (sizeAndVal & 0x1)
5143  {
5144  if (shortAddr == (FTDF_ShortAddress)(saPart & 0x0000ffff))
5145  {
5146  *entry = i;
5147  *shortAddrIdx = 0;
5148  return FTDF_TRUE;
5149  }
5150  }
5151 
5152  if (sizeAndVal & 0x2)
5153  {
5154  if (shortAddr == (FTDF_ShortAddress)((saPart >> 16) & 0x0000ffff))
5155  {
5156  *entry = i;
5157  *shortAddrIdx = 1;
5158  return FTDF_TRUE;
5159  }
5160  }
5161 
5162  saPart = FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, i);
5163 
5164  if (sizeAndVal & 0x4)
5165  {
5166  if (shortAddr == (FTDF_ShortAddress)(saPart & 0x0000ffff))
5167  {
5168  *entry = i;
5169  *shortAddrIdx = 2;
5170  return FTDF_TRUE;
5171  }
5172  }
5173 
5174  if (sizeAndVal & 0x8)
5175  {
5176  if (shortAddr == ((FTDF_ShortAddress)(saPart >> 16) & 0x0000ffff))
5177  {
5178  *entry = i;
5179  *shortAddrIdx = 3;
5180  return FTDF_TRUE;
5181  }
5182  }
5183  }
5184 
5185  return FTDF_FALSE;
5186 }
5187 
5188 FTDF_Boolean FTDF_fpprLookupExtAddress(FTDF_ExtAddress extAddr, uint8_t *entry)
5189 {
5190  uint8_t i;
5191  uint32_t sizeAndVal;
5192  uint32_t extAddrHi, extAddrLo;
5193  extAddrHi = (uint32_t)((extAddr >> 32) & 0xffffffff);
5194  extAddrLo = (uint32_t)(extAddr & 0xffffffff);
5195 
5196  for (i = 0; i < FTDF_FPPR_TABLE_ENTRIES; i++)
5197  {
5198  sizeAndVal = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_SIZE_AND_VAL, i);
5199 
5200  /* Check if there is a valid extended address. */
5201  if (sizeAndVal != 0x1)
5202  {
5203  continue;
5204  }
5205 
5206  if ((extAddrLo == FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_L, i)) &&
5207  (extAddrHi == FTDF_GET_FIELD_INDEXED(FP_PROCESSING_RAM_EXP_SA_H, i)))
5208  {
5209  *entry = i;
5210  return FTDF_TRUE;
5211  }
5212  }
5213 
5214  return FTDF_FALSE;
5215 }
5216 
5217 #endif /* FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE == FTDF_FP_BIT_MODE_AUTO */
5218

5222  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_FP_OVERRIDE, fpOverride ? 1 : 0);
5223  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_FP_FORCE_VALUE, fpForce ? 1 : 0);
5224 }

5226 #if FTDF_FP_BIT_TEST_MODE

5228 {
5229  *matchFp = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_ADDR_TAB_MATCH_FP_VALUE) ? FTDF_TRUE : FTDF_FALSE;
5230  *fpOverride = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_FP_OVERRIDE) ? FTDF_TRUE : FTDF_FALSE;
5231  *fpForce = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_FP_FORCE_VALUE) ? FTDF_TRUE : FTDF_FALSE;
5232 }

5246 
5247 #if FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF
5248 
5249 static inline void FTDF_sdbSaveState(void)
5250 {
5251  volatile uint32_t *txFifoPtr = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_FIFO);
5252  uint32_t *dstPtr = (uint32_t *) FTDF_sdb.buffer;
5253  uint8_t word_length_rem;
5254 
5255  FTDF_sdb.nrOfBackoffs = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_NB_STAT);
5256 
5257  /* Read first 4 bytes. */
5258  *dstPtr++ = *txFifoPtr++;
5259 
5260  ASSERT_WARNING((FTDF_sdb.buffer[0] >= 3) && (FTDF_sdb.buffer[0] < FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH));
5261  /* The length is the buffer length excluding the length byte itself */
5262  word_length_rem = (FTDF_sdb.buffer[0] + 4) / 4 - 1; /* 1 word we already read */
5263 
5264  while (word_length_rem--)
5265  {
5266  *dstPtr++ = *txFifoPtr++;
5267  }
5268 
5269  FTDF_sdb.metadata0 = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0,
5270  FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
5271  FTDF_sdb.metadata1 = *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR_INDEXED(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1,
5272  FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
5273  FTDF_sdb.phyCsmaCaAttr = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYCSMACAATTR);
5274 }
5275 
5276 static inline void FTDF_sdbResume(void)
5277 {
5278  volatile uint32_t *txFifoPtr = FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_FIFO);
5279  volatile uint32_t *txFlagSet = FTDF_GET_FIELD_ADDR(ON_OFF_REGMAP_TX_FLAG_SET);
5280  uint32_t *srcPtr = (uint32_t *) FTDF_sdb.buffer;
5281 
5282  uint8_t word_length_rem;
5283 
5284  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_NB_VAL, FTDF_sdb.nrOfBackoffs);
5285 
5286  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_RESUME_SET, 1);
5287 
5288  ASSERT_WARNING((FTDF_sdb.buffer[0] >= 3) && (FTDF_sdb.buffer[0] < FTDF_BUFFER_LENGTH));
5289 
5290  /* The length is the buffer length excluding the length byte itself */
5291  word_length_rem = (FTDF_sdb.buffer[0] + 4) / 4;
5292 
5293  while (word_length_rem--)
5294  {
5295  *txFifoPtr++ = *srcPtr++;
5296  }
5297 
5298  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_PHYCSMACAATTR, FTDF_sdb.phyCsmaCaAttr);
5299 
5300  *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_0) = FTDF_sdb.metadata0;
5301 
5302  *FTDF_GET_REG_ADDR(RETENTION_RAM_TX_META_DATA_1) = FTDF_sdb.metadata1;
5303 
5304  *txFlagSet |= (1 << FTDF_TX_DATA_BUFFER);
5305 }
5306 
5307 static inline void FTDF_sdbReset(void)
5308 {
5309  FTDF_SET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_RESUME_CLEAR, 1);
5310 }
5311 
5312 static inline void FTDF_sdbSetCCARetryTime(void)
5313 {
5314  FTDF_Time timestamp = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
5315  FTDF_Time boStat = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_CSMA_CA_BO_STAT) *
5316  FTDF_UNIT_BACKOFF_PERIOD;
5317  FTDF_sdb.ccaRetryTime = timestamp + boStat;
5318 }
5319

5323  FTDF_sdb.state = FTDF_SDB_STATE_INIT;

5326 void FTDF_sdbFsmBackoffIRQ(void)
5327 {
5328 #if !defined(FTDF_NO_CSL) || !defined(FTDF_NO_TSCH)
5329 
5330  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled || FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
5331  {
5332  return;
5333  }
5334 
5335 #endif
5336 
5337  switch (FTDF_sdb.state)
5338  {
5339  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_RESUMING:
5340  FTDF_sdbReset();
5341 
5342  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_INIT:
5343  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_BACKING_OFF:
5344  FTDF_sdbSetCCARetryTime();
5345  FTDF_sdb.state = FTDF_SDB_STATE_BACKING_OFF;
5346  break;
5347 
5348  default:
5349  ASSERT_WARNING(0);
5350  }
5351 }

5360  }
5361 
5362 #endif

5367  FTDF_sdbSaveState();
5368  FTDF_sdb.state = FTDF_SDB_STATE_WAITING_WAKE_UP_IRQ;
5369  break;
5370 
5371  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_INIT:
5372  break;
5373 
5374  default:
5375  ASSERT_WARNING(0);
5376  }
5377 }

5488 
5489 FTDF_USec FTDF_sdbGetSleepTime(void)
5490 {
5491  FTDF_USec sleepTime = ~((FTDF_USec) 0);
5492 #if !defined(FTDF_NO_CSL) || !defined(FTDF_NO_TSCH)
5493 
5494  if (FTDF_pib.leEnabled || FTDF_pib.tschEnabled)
5495  {
5496  return sleepTime;
5497  }
5498 
5499 #endif
5500 
5501  switch (FTDF_sdb.state)
5502  {
5503  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_INIT:
5504  {
5505  if ((FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_LMACREADY4SLEEP) == 0) || FTDF_reqCurrent)
5506  {
5507  sleepTime = 0;
5508  }
5509  else
5510  {
5511  sleepTime = ~((FTDF_USec) 0);
5512  }
5513 
5514  break;
5515  }
5516 
5517  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_BACKING_OFF:
5518  {
5519  FTDF_Time currentTime = FTDF_GET_FIELD(ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL);
5520 
5521  if (currentTime <= FTDF_sdb.ccaRetryTime)
5522  {
5523  sleepTime = (FTDF_sdb.ccaRetryTime - currentTime) * 16;
5524  }
5525  else
5526  {
5527  sleepTime = (1 << SIZE_F_FTDF_ON_OFF_REGMAP_SYMBOLTIMESNAPSHOTVAL - 1) -
5528  (currentTime + FTDF_sdb.ccaRetryTime) * 16;
5529  }
5530 
5531  if (sleepTime > 256 * FTDF_UNIT_BACKOFF_PERIOD * 16)
5532  {
5533  /* We have exceeded the CCA retry time. Abort sleep and wait for Tx IRQ. */
5534  sleepTime = 0;
5535  }
5536 
5537  break;
5538  }
5539 
5540  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_RESUMING:
5541  sleepTime = 0;
5542  break;
5543 
5544  case FTDF_SDB_STATE_WAITING_WAKE_UP_IRQ:
5545  sleepTime = ~((FTDF_USec) 0);
5546  break;
5547 
5548  default:
5549  ASSERT_WARNING(0);
5550  }
5551 
5552  return sleepTime;
5553 }
5554 
5555 #endif /* FTDF_USE_SLEEP_DURING_BACKOFF */
5556 
5557 #endif /* #if dg_configBLACK_ORCA_IC_REV != BLACK_ORCA_IC_REV_A */
5558 
5559 #if dg_configUSE_FTDF_DDPHY == 1
5560 void FTDF_ddphySet(uint16_t ccaReg)
5561 {
5562  FTDF_criticalVar();
5563  FTDF_enterCritical();
5564  /* We use the critical section here as protection for the global variable and the HW sleep
5565  * state. */
5566  FTDF_ddphyCcaReg = ccaReg;
5567 
5568  /* Apply immediately if block is up. */
5569  if (REG_GETF(CRG_TOP, PMU_CTRL_REG, FTDF_SLEEP) == 0x0)
5570  {
5571  FTDF_DPHY->DDPHY_CCA_REG = FTDF_ddphyCcaReg;
5572  }
5573 
5574  FTDF_exitCritical();
5575 }
5576 
5577 void FTDF_ddphyRestore(void)
5578 {
5579  if (FTDF_ddphyCcaReg)
5580  {
5581  /* Apply immediately if block is up. */
5582  FTDF_criticalVar();
5583  FTDF_enterCritical();
5584  ASSERT_WARNING(REG_GETF(CRG_TOP, PMU_CTRL_REG, FTDF_SLEEP) == 0x0);
5585  FTDF_DPHY->DDPHY_CCA_REG = FTDF_ddphyCcaReg;
5586  FTDF_exitCritical();
5587  }
5588 }
5589 
5590 void FTDF_ddphySave(void)

5594  FTDF_enterCritical();
5595  ASSERT_WARNING(REG_GETF(CRG_TOP, PMU_CTRL_REG, FTDF_SLEEP) == 0x0);
5596  FTDF_ddphyCcaReg = FTDF_DPHY->DDPHY_CCA_REG;
5597  FTDF_exitCritical();
5598 }
